INSERT INTO `documents` VALUES (1,4,2,'Overview','An analysis has many spreadsheets.\r\nSave as creates copy of analysis\r\nMultiple authorities\r\nView menu shows same as Learner Level, Course Level, Top Level\r\nLearner Level has button to create filter\r\nImport management - each spreadsheet upload flags records so each upload can be processed as one unit\r\nManagement lookups - lots of tabs one for each table\r\nIs it possible to embed pdf in page?\r\nImport formats can vary - determined by aid files (xml)','2009-11-24 15:46:03'),(2,4,2,'Import Spreadsheet','File uploaded using paperclip in Import Learner Data.\r\nFile then needs processing.\r\n\r\nIt creates:\r\nLearners, Courses, Venues, Providers, Tutors, CourseCodes.\r\n\r\nUsing spreadsheet gem http://spreadsheet.rubyforge.org/GUIDE_txt.html for reading spreadsheet as roo caused encoding errors as it required hpricot for google spreadsheet reading.\r\n','2009-12-15 14:03:00'),(3,6,2,'Useful Documents','','2009-12-21 18:28:08'),(5,32,2,'Initial design','Each agent will have a separate url, which will use that agents branding for all pages.\r\nOnly allow login of users linked to that agent.\r\nAn Agent has many companies and investors.\r\n\r\nA site may belong to either a company, investor or agent.\r\nA site has many addresses and contacts which has many telecoms.\r\n\r\nAn investor has and belongs to may investors.\r\n\r\nThe html fields on document, template and dashboard will have a html editor e.g. TinyMCE\r\n\r\nThe dashboard would not be dynamic, just uploaded images of charts.\r\n\r\nA Company user would be taken to dashboard on login, an admin would be taken to the admin home(user list)\r\n\r\nReminder dropdown on event is the time before event the user/investors should be reminded.\r\n\r\nIf an admin users the select link on the user list they will be taken to the users home page and only have the rights of the user except the admin link in menu bar is still available and clicking will return the admin rights and show the user list.\r\n','2011-05-24 11:18:55'),(8,50,2,'ART Tool Documentation','https://www.dropbox.com/sh/dad0623m8ktsrb8/AADZjPvumQPC1umzRoa2zSmKa?dl=0','2015-02-18 15:37:28');
