arly with regard to usability and appeal. I would like it to become the iPhone of land valuation software ;-)\r\n\r\nI would particularly like it to calculate Interest calculations on-the-fly (i.e. Work out the cashflow as the user types)\r\n\r\nI would then envisage it linking with a database of suppliers and providing a total solution to a novice property developer could:\r\n\r\n1. Develop their appraisal\r\n2. Look at suppliers in their area together with genuine user reviews of those suppliers\r\n3. Commission suppliers through the software\r\n\r\nSuppliers include carpenters, plumbers, builders, lenders etc\r\n\r\nThere would also need to be a business model. The software needs massive take-up to be useful and we could not charge any kind of up-front fee. I think it is also vital that suppliers cannot pay to have a better chance of being used. I would want it to give genuine information, not be a sales pitch. So at this point I don\'t quite know how it would make money. Any suggestions with this regard would be gratefully received.\r\n\r\nSo, first of all a review of the whole concept (development platform etc) before we get stuck in.',NULL,NULL,5,6,11,NULL,6,1,'2010-01-18 18:19:35','2010-03-11 17:06:33','2010-01-18',0,NULL,NULL,69,1,2,0,NULL),(70,2,16,'Obtain HMRC recognition for eSubmission and eP45','','2010-07-30',NULL,12,NULL,16,NULL,6,7,'2010-01-18 18:21:02','2015-03-04 12:09:37','2010-03-11',0,4,NULL,70,1,2,0,NULL),(71,4,20,'Spoof a load of test data into quickhaul and put the system through its paces','Put quickfuel through it\'s paces including a load of test data. Try to make the data look realistic as I would like to give people a good idea of how it works at meetings. Please do the same for GoGet.\r\n\r\nPlease fix any issues that arise, be they shop-stopping bugs, spelling mistakes, tuning issues or general improvements.\r\n\r\nasssume you mean quickhaul. Amending postcode processing to use google post code lookup processing. Help messages need wri