NULL,NULL,337,1,2,0,NULL),(338,2,4,'1190 Build the pivot table system as per our discussions (phase 1)','Sounds really good!\r\n\r\nIt might be worth seeing if there could be an option to choose between count and sum for the data in the middle, and possibly look to see if we could vary the data in the middle (i.e. learners or enrolments or venues or courses etc). However this could be a version two if it is tough to figure out on the first run (the version below will already bring great results, particularly combined with the enhanced postcode fields).\r\n\r\nThanks\r\n\r\nMatthew\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n________________________________________\r\nFrom: Tony Harris [t.harris@terrabase.co.uk]\r\nSent: 29 March 2011 11:11\r\nTo: SMITH, Matthew (Education)\r\nSubject: Pivot table solution\r\n\r\nHi Matt\r\n\r\nWe think we have a simple and elegant potential solution for the ALDAS\r\npivot table analysis system we were discussing.\r\n\r\nThe solution would be very similar to the Quickfilter™ except the Field\r\ndrop-down would be replaced by a second Category drop-down. The first\r\ncategory drop-down would be named Column Category and the second one\r\nwould be named Row Category (or the other way round depending upon what\r\nis more intuitive).\r\n\r\nThe grid would then be populated with data broken down between the two\r\ncategories.\r\n\r\nFor instance:\r\n\r\nIf the user selected Ethnicity for the Column Category and Priority for\r\nthe Row Category they would be presented with something like:\r\n\r\nEthnicity 1 Ethnicity 2 Ethnicity 3...\r\nPriority 1 #### #### ####\r\nPriority 2 #### #### ####\r\nPriority 3 #### #### ####\r\n...\r\n\r\nWhere the hashes refer to learner counts.\r\n\r\nWe could probably even include an output drop-down to include other\r\nresults beyond counts. eg. Retention, Achievement etc.\r\n',NULL,22,5,6,16,22,6,4,'2011-03-30 12:37:20','2012-08-31 16:02:08','2011-03-30',0,NULL,NULL,338,1,2,0,NULL),(339,2,30,'1191 Updates to Book Now Page','Put this pa