/edit and delete users.\r\n\r\nThe add/edit user should be in a sub-pop-up again styled as per the image in dropbox though including a password confirmation field under password.\r\nClicking OK saves the record and closes the sub-pop-up, clicking Cancel closes the sub-pop-up without saving the record.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL,5,6,6,NULL,6,7,'2013-07-02 17:39:37','2013-07-29 18:29:53',NULL,100,NULL,NULL,1115,1,2,0,NULL),(1116,2,48,'User management list in pop-up','Clicking Users on the home page should open a pop-up with the list of users styled as in the attached image.\r\n\r\nThe green \"User group (all users) >\" is a drop-down with a list of the valid groups (roles) all users, Meta Administrator, Administrator and Lecturer. selecting anything other than all users should filter the user list to only show users that are in the selected group.\r\n\r\nThe search box should filter on username and email showing all users that have the entered characters anywhere in their username or email.\r\n\r\nThe green \"Sort by (username) >\" is a drop-down with a list of username and email. This controls which column the users should be sorted by.\r\n\r\nThe email should be a mailto link.\r\n\r\nThe pop-up should be a fixed height. Once the user list overflows there should be a scrollbar on the right to allow a user to scroll up and down the list.\r\n\r\nThe Meta Administrator cannot be deleted but in all other respects is an Administrator.\r\n\r\nOnly Administrators can access user management and add/edit and delete users.\r\n\r\nThe Add/Edit functionality with be described in another issue.',NULL,NULL,5,21,11,NULL,6,6,'2013-07-02 17:52:52','2013-07-29 11:03:19','2013-07-02',0,NULL,NULL,1116,1,2,0,NULL),(1117,2,48,'Add/edit user in a sub-pop-up','The \"Add new user...\" and \"Edit\" links on the user management list pop-up should open a sub-pop-up styled as in the attached image.\r\n\r\nThere should be a password confirmation field under the password field.\r\n\r\nValidation errors should be shown in the sub-pop-up.\r\n\r\nClicking OK saves the record and closes the sub-pop-up, clicking Cancel closes the sub-pop-up without saving the record. In either case the user should be on the user management pop-up with the added/edited user details showing in the list.\r\n\r\nThe Edit User title should be Add User if creating a new user.\r\n\r\nThe green \"User type (Administrator) >\" is a drop-down listing the groups (Meta Administrator, Administrator and Lecturer).\r\n\r\nThe existing Tutor option becomes Lecturer.\r\n\r\nThe sub-pop-up should be added in Jquery when the main pop-up is opened (i.e. processDialog). \r\nEnsure you destroy the sup-pop-up once you have closed it so that stale data is not shown if there are network problems when the user next adds/edits a user.\r\nAdd a class to the sub-pop-up in the dialog params so that you can style the main and sub-pop-ups differently.',NULL,NULL,5,21,6,NULL,6,11,'2013-07-02 18:06:18','2013-07-26 18:08:58','2013-07-02',0,NULL,NULL,1117,1,2,0,NULL),(1118,2,4,'Allow dashboard to work in an iframe with the default analysis','Amend the dashboard to allow direct access from the IPMS portal in an Iframe.\r\n\r\nDo not require an analysis to be selected just use the default analysis. If there is no default analysis just show a message.\r\n\r\nStore the quick-filter filter id in a separate session variable, so that if the user is logged into Aldas with a filter applied it does not affect the filter on the widget view of the dashboard.',NULL,28,5,6,6,NULL,6,3,'2013-07-02 18:57:10','2013-07-04 18:45:47','2013-07-02',100,NULL,NULL,1118,1,2,0,NULL),(1119,1,46,'After clicking \'Logout\' on toolbar the resulting page says Log In, but it is not a link','It looks like you should be able to click Log in, but it is unlinked text',NULL,NULL,5,6,6,NULL,3,6,'2013-07-03 11:02:53','2013-08-02 17:41:59','2013-07-03',100,NULL,NULL,1119,1,2,0,NULL),(1120,2,36,'Try out the Cefter Moodle reporting plug-in','',NULL,NULL,5,6,6,NULL,