ypes can be managed. The delivered solution includes the necessary hosting requirements including SSL certification so that all data-transfer through the Internet is encrypted. We will provide any training you need, both onsite and over the phone/email.\r\n\r\n2. Slik Promo Tailored Booking System\r\n\r\nSlik Promo need to be able to match, from a wide selection, suitable staff for jobs, some of which may have fairly vague information with regard to shift times or even venue locations. They need to be able to create jobs based on all the information available at the time and easily select the staff to whom they wish to offer the work. To this end the system contains an easily filterable, sortable and searchable \'infinity\' grid of all the jobs on the system. An \'infinity\' grid is a type of grid that expands the number of records in it as you scroll down, similar to the way Facebook and other modern applications work. The grid can be sortable by any of the columns we choose to include, for instance most recent jobs can be shown at the top, or jobs can be listed alphabetically by client name, or number of staff involved etc. The grid also includes a quick-filtering system where you can for example, choose to only show jobs from a particular client, or jobs in a particular region, or current jobs that have not yet been completed etc. The grid also includes a free-type search facility where only jobs matching the text are shown, which happens in real-time as you type, giving you an instant response as you search through the data. The free-text is mapped to search through any fields we choose, such as client name, staff member name, job ID etc. Using this system staff will be able to quickly find any job they need to view, and once found are able to work with it in a variety of ways. One option is to make a copy of an existing job as the basis for a new job, with all the same staff already included (these can be edited before the job is confirmed), and all the information already in place apart from aspects which are bound to change such as dates. Existing jobs can be edited of course, and removed if required, \r\n\r\nThe job creation system gives as much power to the user as possible. For example, if specific shift times are not yet known, you do not need to enter this information and there is space where you can describe expected shift times in a free-type method allowing for a more nuanced approach. This philosophy is applied throughout the job creation and staff profiling system to make the solution as flexible and organic as possible.\r\n\r\nWhen a job is created and confirmed, the information is sent out to the assigned staff who can then email back their acceptance of the job or otherwise. An option is to allow staff to accept the job from within the system and allow them to confirm the actual work done after it is completed. To do this staff are able to see a list of all their jobs and are able to go into them and enter information. They also have a list of all the work they have carried out and any upcoming jobs.\r\n\r\n3. Enhanced Staff Selection System\r\n\r\nThe system includes an \'infinity\' grid of staff which has all the filtering, sorting and searching facilities available in the job booking system so that it is easy for you to find recently used staff, or staff with a good reputation, or staff who suit a particular job type. It is possible to select one or many staff on the grid and click a button to create a new job with these staff already assigned. This makes it very fast and simple to match the best staff to the job. However, the staff grid can also be included in the job creation system so if you need to add more staff to the job, or you create the job from scratch, you can easily add more staff to it using the familiar process.\r\n\r\nThe staff can be emailed from within the system by clicking a button to email all those selected. This can be done from within the jobs screen too, sending an email out to all the staff assigned to that job.\r\n\r\nOne option is to include a messaging system within the solution itself so that all communications with staff can be seen against their profiles.\r\n\r\n4. Staff Self-profiling System\r\n\r\nOnce a new staff sign-up has taken place and they have created their basic account they can start to fill it out with all the details you require including a selection of photos. They have full control over their profile and the photos they upload, which are available to you to download in their original resolution. We can also include an upload facility for any other documents they might want to add such as CVs or a portfolio in pdf format etc.\r\n\r\nWe can include a facility allowing staff to keep track of their account as it is processed by Slik Promo, so they know if documents are waiting to be signed or whether they have accepted the terms and conditions etc. We can also include a messaging system from the point of view of the staff member so they can see their communications with Slik Promo, and a history/preview of jobs, as explained above.\"','2014-11-26',NULL,5,6,6,NULL,3,9,'2014-10-27 16:55:40','2014-12-02 18:54:27','2014-10-27',0,NULL,NULL,1335,1,2,0,NULL),(1336,2,15,'Create plan with costs for manual fail-over server as discussed','I guess the server should work on subdomain versions of our domains:\r\n\r\neg www2.imperialhorizons.org\r\n\r\nIf the main server fails we can fire up the backup server and the user should be able to manually put in the server2 URL and carry on from the last sync\r\n\r\nI was thinking perhaps syncing once around 12:30pm (i.e. lunchtime) and once during the nightly backup around 3am providing this had no significant performance hit on the main server.\r\n',NULL,NULL,5,6,11,NULL,3,5,'2014-10-29 14:17:50','2014-11-07 17:24:14','2014-10-29',0,NULL,NULL,1336,1,2,0,NULL),(1337,1,48,'Selecting year 3/4 in the All export only exports year 3 students','',NULL,NULL,5,6,7,NULL,6,7,'2014-11-05 12:55:29','2014