pancy in the learner count is due to having 2 enrolments for the same postcode and date of birth but for different names (Andy Hatton and Will Roberts).\r\n\r\nThe number of learners is determined by the count of distinct date of birth and learner postcode so Aldas considers them the same learner.\r\n\r\nThe GLH discrepancy is probably due to the GLH on the top level report being calculated from the slh.\r\n\r\nIt calculates the average slh (sum(slh)/  count(learners.id) as average_slh) for each course then totals those values to give the total GLH. None of the GLH figures are used. \r\n\r\nI know this has been discussed before and that it should no longer be calculated from slh.\r\nThere is the issue 1041 for the change but it is priority 9 so has not been done yet and as its 2 years old I am not sure if the changes are still correct.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOn 02/03/15 16:55, Tony Harris wrote:\r\n\r\n\r\nTony Harris \r\nTerrabase Ltd \r\nCompany No 4612938 (England and Wales) \r\nReg Office 2nd Floor Refuge House, 33-37 Watergate Row \r\nChester. CH1 2LE \r\nt 01244 881657 \r\ne t.harris@terrabase.co.uk \r\nw www.terrabase.co.uk \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n------ Forwarded Message ------ \r\nFrom: \"SMITH, Matthew (Education)\" <Matthew.Smith@cheshirewestandchester.gov.uk> \r\nTo: \"t.harris@terrabase.co.uk\" <t.harris@terrabase.co.uk> \r\nSent: 02/03/2015 16:53:46 \r\nSubject: FW: Potential ALDAS issues \r\n\r\nAnd the next problem! \r\n\r\nMatthew Smith \r\n\r\nSenior Officer - Learner Data and Research \r\n\r\nSkills and Employment team \r\n\r\nGrowth & Prosperity \r\n\r\nCheshire West and Chester Council \r\n\r\n\r\nTel: 0151 35(66718) \r\n\r\nEmail: matthew.smith@cheshirewestandchester.gov.uk \r\n\r\nLocation: Civic Building, 4 Civic Way, Ellesmere Port, CH65 0BE \r\n\r\nVisit:www.cheshirewestandchester.gov.uk \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n‘Make sure you are registered to vote’ \r\n\r\n\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------- \r\nFrom: RAVEN, Michae