re. Having re-checked the spreadsheet, I still can\'t find anything to dissuade me from the manual count figure. Example: Project Code W4002 includes 29 unique learners for the Autumn term, but ALDAS will only register 28 unique learners. The enrolment figure for both is 29. \r\nThere are also several instances where the GLH figure is lower on ALDAS than it is for the manual count. Again, having checked the spreadsheet and the course codes, I\'m inclined to say that it\'s the ALDAS figure that\'s incorrect. More often than not, this discrepancy occurs when there\'s a decimal point involved in the manual count GLH figure. Furthermore, when I manually calculate the GLH from the Courses tab on ALDAS it will match the manual count figure, but not the GLH total on the ALDAS top level report (so it\'s as if ALDAS is surreptitiously agreeing with the manual count!) Example: Project Code W4006 has a GLH of 55 (and an SLH of 275). ALDAS only registers a GLH of 54 on the Top Level Report (and an SLH of 270). However, when I add up the GLH of all the courses listed on the ALDAS Courses tab, it equals 55, not 54. \r\nCould this be a potential .aid file issue? \r\n\r\n\r\nMike \r\n\r\nMichael Raven \r\n\r\nLifelong Learning Performance Monitoring Officer \r\n\r\nEconomic Growth & Prosperity Team \r\n\r\nCheshire East Council \r\n\r\n\r\nTel: 0151 35(66905) \r\n\r\nEmail: michael.raven@cheshireeast.gov.uk \r\n\r\nLocation: 2nd Floor, Civic Building, 4 Civic Way, Ellesmere Port, CH65 0BE \r\n\r\nVisit:www.cheshireeast.gov.uk \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n************************************************************************ \r\nDisclaimer: \r\n\r\nIf you are not the intended recipient of this email (and any attachment), please inform the sender by return email and destroy all copies. Unauthorised access, use, disclosure, storage or copying is not permitted. \r\nThe views expressed by the author do not necessarily reflect the views or policies of Cheshire West and Chester Borough C