e was. \r\n\r\nWhen a Company user is deactivated, the associated company will no longer be visible, and will not appear in the agent or investors lists. No email reminders for events, etc. will be sent. \r\n\r\nWhen an Investor user is deactivated, the associated investor will no longer be visible in the companies investors list and will no longer receive emails from any company. \r\n\r\nWhen an Agent user is deactivated, all the associated companies will be transferred to the default Adagio agent. \r\n\r\nShould deactivated users details be kept forever? what are the implications under the Data Protection Act? \r\n\r\n4.29 Agent Home \r\nThe Contact Name, Telephone and Email are the investor relations details not the CEO\'s. \r\nShould the Email address be a mail_to link? \r\n\r\n4.32, 4.20 New Account \r\nThe notes say a company user will be notified of the pricing terms and are then taken to the Add/Edit Company Profile screen if they agree to them. \r\nShould this just be a page with text (to be specified) and two links/buttons at the bottom to say Accept or Decline? what happens if they decline? I assume to user would be deleted? \r\nOr should it be a check-box on the new account page to say \"I have read and accept the pricing terms\" with a link to the pricing terms page? \r\n\r\n\r\nGeneral \r\nThe new cookie law should allow the session cookie we require for authentication purposes, but if the remember me option is used a permanent cookie would be required, is clicking the remember me option acceptable as giving permission. \r\nGoogle Analytics also requires a cookie. The privacy policy should include details of cookie usage and data retention.  \r\n \r\n','2011-10-24 11:41:00',0),(2192,448,'Issue',13,'comment posted by Tony on 12.09.2011 11:59    edit   delete \r\nPut Acc Succ figure into accredited achievement section as a double check that the figures are correct \r\n','2011-10-24 11:43:50',0),(2193,449,'Issue',13,'comment posted by Patrick on 12.07.201