e changes.\r\n\r\nAdded action types, action categories and sources to manage lookups. These will need improving to add pagination, searching sorting etc.\r\n\r\nAmended add action form to use dropdowns for action type, category and source.\r\n\r\nAmended dialog to be fixed size.\r\n\r\nAdded styling to action list (lookups and users have same styling). Action list can now be filtered an action type.\r\n\r\nImproved dialog handling and fixed some issues.\r\n\r\nIf anything weird happens with the dialogs or they stop responding refresh the age and try again. I will work on preventing weirdness and lack of response.\r\n\r\nOnly tested in firefox 7.0.1.\r\n\r\nDocuments and reports are still outstanding, sorting the dialogs took longer than I thought. Actions and Notes still only work when editing a provider. There is still no link to the project provider. ','2011-11-09 21:13:45',0),(2397,612,'Issue',16,'','2011-11-10 17:07:26',0),(2398,612,'Issue',3,'','2011-11-11 11:10:33',0),(2399,599,'Issue',3,'','2011-11-11 11:16:12',0),(2400,599,'Issue',3,'Put into dropbox','2011-11-11 11:16:30',0),(2401,379,'Issue',6,'Released latest changes.\r\n\r\nEvent recurrence now works for all options and validates everything. Formatting corrected when validation fails.\r\n\r\nThe investors list for a company and the homepage for an investor both show the email address when the company/investor is awaiting confirmation.\r\n\r\nThe company, investor and agent profiles now show a change password link instead of the password and password confirmation fields, the fields reappear when the link is clicked.\r\n\r\nThe investor profile is showing fine for me(FF7.0.1), Could you re-check and give details if there is still a problem.\r\nThe invite investor shows the correct width for me(FF7.0.1).','2011-11-11 13:38:11',0),(2402,379,'Issue',3,'The invite investor screen seems to be correct now, but the investor profile was still cutting it off:\r\n\r\nhttp://www.terrabase.co.uk/adagio_edge/users/16/edit\r\n\r\n','2011-11-11 13:55:26',0),(2403,613,'Issue',3,'Analysis\r\n\r\nThis fault is intermittent and difficult to investigate because of the number of variables (anti-virus, firewall, IIS configuration, TCP/IP configuration, router firewall, IPv6 vs IPv4 configuration, SQL Server Configuration, Windows 7 networking settings etc. All these variables interplay and require hours of work to investigate as new computers are set-up and installed and appear to work, only to not work next time the network is put together with a different router. The e-volve technical support team had no facility to emulate the set-up we use and only have a virtual representation of the system.\r\n\r\nMany hours have been spent on the phone to the e-volve support team as they suggest possible solutions with firewall configurations and router types. These solutions sometimes appeared to work, as over a period of time the computers would make the connection. However, the connection would soon drop again and the software itself would show other symptoms and unexpected error messages as the connection dropped in and out.\r\n\r\nI continued the investigations without e-volve support and took advantage of my software development skills, and knowing something of the foibles of Microsoft SQL Server and IIS I was able to pin it down to changing IP addresses of the computers each time a network was created. This should not be an issue, but Microsoft often use non-standard, proprietary procedures to underpin their software and this seemed to be the case here.\r\n\r\nThe solution seemed to be to fix the IPs of all the computers, but I was unable to do this within Windows as the computers need to be able to obtain an assigned external IP when they connect to the Internet so this left configuring the routers to fix the IPs and leave the computers to allow their IPs to be assigned externally.\r\n\r\nAnother issue with the system is that the tutors like to be able to give their learners results immediately. The new system requires Internet access to enable this.\r\n\r\nThe existing routers do not all provide the facility to be programmed to assign IP addresses, I haven\'t checked them all, but certainly the blue Linksys ones do not.','2011-11-11 14:19:03',0),(2404,613,'Issue',3,'Design\r\n\r\nThe solution is to programme each network\'s router to identify each computer on the network and assign a known IP address to that computer such that it never changes, this way SQL Server always communicates and does not get confused. To this end routers which allow this kind of programming need to be used across the networks and then programmed to recognise their associated computers.\r\n\r\nSuitable Internet access can be provided by a Vodafone \'dongle\' using the mobile data network.\r\n\r\nThe Netgear MBRN3000 router £66.99+VAT from Insight provides a robust, high quality router which can be programmed appropriately, and has the facility to plug in a Vodafone \'dongle\' which means all the machines on the network can have Internet access if required, which opens up further pedagogical possibilities as well as solving the reliability and instant results issues.\r\n\r\nI can supply the routers and dongles. The dongles currently cost £19 each from Vodafone with a £5 per month charge giving 500mb of data which is plenty for expected usage patterns. The dongle \'contract\' can be cancelled on demand.\r\n\r\nFrom a tutor\'s point of view the network would be set-up in exactly the same way as the Promissor system apart from plugging a \'dongle\' into the router if they want Internet access.\r\n','2011-11-11 14:28:56',0),(2405,379,'Issue',6,'Add/Edit Document now has a dropdown of unpublished events.\r\nCan an event be linked to more than one document?\r\n\r\nPublishing an event sets the release date of the associated document.\r\n\r\nInvestors can only see published documents, (event is published or no event linked)\r\n\r\nInvestors homepage now shows the next event and next 