ra roles. They may need to logout and back in to see the new rights.','2012-02-27 21:16:09',0),(3196,773,'Issue',6,'I have done some investigations with the LAMS server and SCORM packages. LAMS does not support SCORM directly but you can add a link in shared resources or Noticeboard to the player.html in the unzipped SCORM package if the files are accessible to the web. However the grades etc will not be recorded as they would be if hosted in Moodle.\r\n\r\nAnother mentioned in Google searches is to upload the SCORM to Moodle and use the link from Moodle in LAMS but I have not been able to determine a way to get the required link as Moodle POSTs a form to play a SCORM package. \r\n\r\nI have partially tested the FTP setup that Claire requested but have found some errors occur and the exit option in the SCORM package I was testing with did not work( it does in Moodle)  ','2012-02-27 21:30:27',0),(3197,590,'Issue',6,'Create course (anywhere) now redirects to add LAMS lesson when saving.\r\n\r\nUpdate My CV is a bit of a problem I can\'t find a way to link to a document in a users Google Docs. It\'s possible to make a template and upload it to the template store and provide a link which will allow a user to create a CV but if the user click it again they will just be directed to the template to create a new CV again. I can\'t find a way to get a link to the created document.\r\n\r\nIt is possible to add Google Docs as a repository which would allow tutors to add google documents as a resource to courses. You can also then activate portfolios which would allow students to export forum posts, assignments, Glossary entries chat sessions etc. to Google Docs\r\nsee http://docs.moodle.org/20/en/Portfolios for details.\r\n\r\nOther than the above and learner stories the changes are ready for release. I have tested the upgrade to Moodle 2.07 on the Disaster recovery server (when it finally booted) without having any problems. I had a couple of minor issues with the plugins I h