mended/combined in Moodle 2.4 http://tracker.moodle.org/browse/MDL-30615','2012-06-01 18:19:05',0),(3988,847,'Issue',6,'Uses same logic as Add/edit Course from site administration. If there are no categories it will create a miscellaneous category.','2012-06-01 20:04:08',0),(3989,853,'Issue',6,'Fixed under #847','2012-06-01 20:05:10',0),(3990,882,'Issue',6,'Investigation showed that RachAdminALDAS created analysis 1112_CWAC_AUTSPR_Release_3_06_06_12 at 10:09 no errors were reported but the log does not show that anything was returned to the browser. The analysis record was correctly created. At 10:12 the analysis creation was submitted again and this time returned the creation form presumably with the error that the analysis name already existed, a further attempt at 10:13 returned the same result.\r\nAt 10:19 MattAdminALDAS logged in and saw that the analysis existed, he edited the analysis successfully.\r\nAt 10:21 RachAdminALDAS viewed the analysis list and was able to successfully select and edit the analysis. An import was then successfully done.\r\n\r\nThere are no errors and nothing odd was happening on the server, I can see no reason why the original creation did not return a response to the browser. There is nothing else to investigate. I suggest waiting to see if it ever happens again.','2012-06-06 11:55:10',0),(3991,882,'Issue',6,'','2012-06-06 11:58:54',0),(3992,882,'Issue',15,'When you create a new analysis in ALDAS (although I don\'t think this happens in Edge) the processing cirlce comes up for a while and then the browser crashes (or more likely times out?). When you click refresh or back you get an error message as the analysis now exists but you are back in the create analysis screen with the details of a now existing analysis.\r\n\r\nI have had this with both IE (7) and Chrome.','2012-06-06 13:22:17',0),(3993,882,'Issue',3,'','2012-06-06 14:10:22',0),(3994,883,'Issue',3,'','2012-06-06 14:27:43',0),(3995,882,'Issue',6,'When an analysis is created it also copies the associated records from the base analysis. In this case there were 11 age levels, 4 priorities, 24 progressions, 33 regions, 7 rural urbans, 19 ethnicities, 5 completion statuses, 14 disabilities, 10 difficulties, 6 result outcomes, 47 learner filters plus there clauses and 1 filter group.\r\nThis takes a little while to complete and the filter group, which is the last record type to be created, was created at 10:13 which is after the second attempt at creating the record. This also explains the lack of rendering a response to the browser, the browser had changed page already.\r\n\r\nThe user should see the processing please wait message until the creation is complete.\r\nI have now found an error in the apache log at 10:13 which may be related.\r\n  [ pid=19142 file=ext/apache2/Hooks.cpp:656 time=2012-06-06 10:13:52.194 ]:\r\n  Either the vistor clicked on the \'Stop\' button in the web browser, or the visitor\'s connection has stalled and couldn\'t receive the data that Apache is sending to it. As a result, you will probably see a \'Broken Pipe\' error in this log file. Please ignore it, this is normal. You might also want to increase Apache\'s TimeOut configuration option if you experience this problem often.\r\n\r\nApache\'s TimeOut configuration is set at 300 seconds. \r\n\r\nBrowsers may timeout before this\r\n\r\nI think the error is due to the browser sending a post (the create analysis form) being sent again before the first post had finished.\r\n\r\nWe either need users to be patient, or to move the extra record creation into the background processing and return a message to the user that the creation is queued, then poll using javascript until the creation is finished. This allows the browser to get responses and give user feedback. Code would need to be added to ensure the analysis could not be used for anything until all the records were created.  \r\n','2012-06-06 17:02:23',0),(3996,885,'Issue',6,NULL,'2012-06-06 17:23:56',0),(3997,884,'Issue',6,'The delete can take a while as it has to delete all the imports, enrolments, courses, venues, tutors, learner filters, top level reports, age levels, priorities, progressions, regions, rural urbans, ethnicities, completion statuses, disabilities, difficulties, result outcomes, and filter groups. \r\nAs this can take a minute or so, the analysis is marked as deleted, removed from the list and the deletion of the associated records is added to the queue. The user should have a fast response saying the analysis is successfully deleted even though it has only been marked as deleted. \r\n\r\nThe server was probably a little busy with 2 imports on aldas and one on aldas edge when this particular deletion occurred, this may have given an overall slower response. \r\nThe queued deletion may have taken several minutes before it was actually processed but this should not be visible to the user.','2012-06-06 17:32:26',0),(3998,883,'Issue',6,'The import shows as uploaded once it has been created. It should probably say queued as the import is added to the queue as part of the creation.\r\nIf the queue is not empty and especially if there is another import processing it may stay queued for several minutes/hours at the moment it would continue to show as uploaded.\r\n\r\nOnce it reaches the top of the queue it would show as processing and the progress bar would be updated if the user is still on the import enrolment data page.\r\n\r\nI think the best change would be something similar to the report, where you are told of the number of jobs queued and your approximate position in the queue, with this being updated until the import is processing and the progress bar is shown. Uploaded should also be changed to queued. ','2012-06-06 17:39:36',0),(3999,886,'Issue',6,'Added a configuration setting to allow admin to control whether creating a new course defaults to adding a LAMS lesson or not.','2012-06-06 19:17:26',0),(4000,860,'Issue',6,'Link added as requested but you ne