urrent_user.books.find(params[:id])@ instead of @Book.find(params[:id])@ in the show, edit, update and destroy methods it would also prevent a user being able to view, edit or delete books other than their own. \r\n\r\nThe json lines are not currently required as there is nothing yet that requires a json response.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Ruby styleguide https://github.com/styleguide/ruby says to use 2 spaces for indents not tabs. Also its best practice not to leave code commented out, once your happy it works remove the code, you can always retrieve the old code from your version control system.\r\n\r\nReleased to http://www.terrabase.co.uk/purplestar/helloworld','2013-04-18 18:20:10',0),(5730,1074,'Issue',6,'Sophie, the migration\'s could have been included in a single file.\r\n\r\nIf you format the text, for description and review, with blank lines they are lost when viewing the book.\r\n\r\nReleased to http://www.terrabase.co.uk/purplestar/helloworld','2013-04-18 18:23:01',0),(5731,1048,'Issue',3,'Tracey: Thanks very much for the feedback.\r\n\r\nSophie: Could you implement the feedback. I\'m going to approve this issue and create a new issue to implement the feedback Tracey suggests.','2013-04-19 10:41:14',0),(5732,1074,'Issue',3,'Hi Sophie. Just marking it as Not Approved to test out the system, and so you can make the formatting changes as mentioned by Tracey. Then releasing the migration as a single file (not sure what that means, but I guess you\'d understand it).','2013-04-19 10:46:46',0),(5733,1074,'Issue',6,'Sophie, please do not change the existing migration files, the comment was for future reference only. \r\nYou should never change a migration once it has been released as the database keeps track of the migrations that have been run.  ','2013-04-19 10:50:50',0),(5734,148,'Issue',6,'Released to live','2013-04-21 19:48:11',0),(5735,149,'Issue',6,'Released to live','2013-04-21 19:48:11',0),(5736,159,'Issue',6,'Released to live','2013-04-21 19:48:11',0),(5737,885,