.find(params[:id]) in the show, edit, update and destroy methods it would also prevent a user being able to view, edit or delete books other than their own.\r\n\r\nThe json lines are not currently required as there is nothing yet that requires a json response.\r\n\r\nThe Ruby styleguide https://github.com/styleguide/ruby says to use 2 spaces for indents not tabs. Also its best practice not to leave code commented out, once your happy it works remove the code, you can always retrieve the old code from your version control system.\r\n\r\nReleased to http://www.terrabase.co.uk/purplestar/helloworld','2013-04-22 12:55:46',0),(5747,1048,'Issue',21,'','2013-04-22 13:08:23',0),(5748,1075,'Issue',21,'','2013-04-22 13:12:04',0),(5749,1083,'Issue',21,'','2013-04-22 14:48:42',0),(5750,1074,'Issue',21,'','2013-04-22 15:09:15',0),(5751,1074,'Issue',21,'I\'ve edited the view code to fix the line formatting and it seems to show correctly now.\r\n\r\nTracey: Thank you for the information about migrations. I\'ve done the migrations in issue #1076 in the same way (before seeing your comment) but I\'ll do them as one migration in future projects.','2013-04-22 15:10:10',0),(5752,1063,'Issue',6,NULL,'2013-04-22 16:58:28',0),(5753,1068,'Issue',6,'Released to adagio_edge','2013-04-22 17:56:55',0),(5754,1069,'Issue',6,'Released to adagio_edge','2013-04-22 17:57:19',0),(5755,1070,'Issue',6,'Released to adagio_edge','2013-04-22 17:57:43',0),(5756,1071,'Issue',6,'Released to adagio_edge','2013-04-22 17:58:02',0),(5757,1054,'Issue',6,'Released to adagio_edge','2013-04-22 17:58:26',0),(5758,1054,'Issue',3,'','2013-04-23 11:38:34',0),(5759,1068,'Issue',3,'When company operator user type is selected some of the fields are greyed out. Could you make it more obvious they are greyed out (on my screen the grey still looked black so it looked like you could still type in them).\r\n\r\nOther than that, spot on!','2013-04-23 11:44:47',0),(5760,1069,'Issue',3,'After clicking publish the Publish column di