\'dialog_form\'.\r\n\r\nTo enable JQuery UI add the following line to app/assets/javascripts/application.js after the require jquery line.\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n//= require jquery-ui\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nYou should also add suitable styling and images which can be obtained from the JQuery themeroller. http://ui-dev.jquery.com/themeroller/\r\n\r\nAdd the following Coffee script to app/assets/javascripts/dialog.js.coffee. \r\n\r\n<pre>\r\njQuery ->\r\n  popup = $(\"#dialog_form\")\r\n\r\n  popup.dialog(\r\n    autoOpen: false\r\n    modal: true\r\n    minHeight: 330\r\n    height: \'auto\'\r\n    width: 700\r\n    resizable: false\r\n    open: processDialog\r\n  )\r\n\r\n  $(\"a.dialog\").live \'click\', ->\r\n    popup_url = $(this).attr(\'href\')\r\n    popup.load( popup_url + \'.html #container\', ->\r\n      if popup.dialog( \"isOpen\" )\r\n        processDialog()\r\n      else\r\n        popup.dialog(\'open\')\r\n    )\r\n    return false\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nThis adds a dialog to the dialog_form div and says all links with class \'dialog\' should load the href of the link and add the contents of the container div  to the dialog. It then opens the dialog unless the dialog is already open in which case it calls the process dialog function. You should add the dialog class to the edit and new links.\r\n\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nprocessDialog = ->\r\n  popup = $(\"#dialog_form\")\r\n  popup.dialog(\'option\', \'position\', [\'center\', \'center\'])\r\n\r\n  popup.find(\'.cancel-button\')\r\n    .click ->\r\n      popup.dialog(\'close\')\r\n      return false\r\n  popup.find(\'.dialog_form\').submit ->\r\n    $.ajax(\r\n      type: this.method\r\n      url: this.action\r\n      data: $(this).serialize()\r\n      dataType: \"script\"\r\n      error: errorHandler\r\n    )\r\n    popup.dialog(\'close\')\r\n    return false\r\n\r\nerrorHandler = (xhr, status,error) ->\r\n  $(\"#dialog_form\").dialog(\'open\')\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nThe processDialog function should contain any javascript that should be applied to the newly loaded html. In the example its just handles the form submit via ajax. and causes a link with the class cancel-button to close the dialog.\r\n\r\nYou also need to amend the controller so that if there is a validation error the form with the error messages is presented in the dialog.\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n   def create\r\n     @book = Book.new(params[:book])\r\n    respond_to do |format|\r\n      if @book.save\r\n        flash[:notice] = \"The book was saved successfully.\"\r\n        format.html { redirect_to books_path}\r\n        format.js { render :js => \"window.location = \'#{books_path}\'\" }\r\n      else\r\n        format.html {  render \'new\' }\r\n        format.js { render \'error\' }\r\n      end\r\n     end\r\n   end\r\n\r\n</pre>\r\nThis responds with javascript to change to the list page if the save was successful otherwise it renders an error view.\r\nCreate app/views/books/error.js.erb with the following content.\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n$(\"#dialog_form\").find(\'#container\').html(\"<%= j(render(:partial => \'form\')) %>\");\r\n$(\"#dialog_form\").dialog(\'open\');\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nThis code replaces the contents of container div in the dialog with the form partial which should contain the validation error messages.\r\n\r\nThe same changes need to be done to the update method.\r\n\r\nYou also need to add the dialog_form class to the form.\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<%= form_for(@book, html: {class: \'dialog_form\'}) do |f| %>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n\r\nAn example rails 3.2.13 application, containing this code, is available at https://github.com/railsgirl42/configman.\r\nThis \"commit\":https://github.com/railsgirl42/configman/commit/af68923a3470d6dc84237acb5118b14ee5e95f85 from Sunday 28 April 2013 contains all the code changes required to add dialogs to an existing application. \r\n\r\nIf there are any discrepancies between the above code and the code in the example application, please use the example applications code as that is proven to work. Feel free to download the configman application, or review its code on GitHub, as it has sorting and searching added to the user list and a requirement to login using a before filter. \r\n\r\nLet me know if you need any more explanation or assistance.','2013-04-30 17:28:49',0),(5855,1029,'Issue',3,'','2013-05-01 10:39:47',0),(5856,1053,'Issue',3,'','2013-05-01 10:40:18',0),(5857,1074,'Issue',3,'','2013-05-01 10:42:52',0),(5858,1083,'Issue',21,'','2013-05-01 10:43:35',0),(5859,1074,'Issue',21,'','2013-05-01 10:50:53',0),(5860,1077,'Issue',21,'','2013-05-01 10:51:46',0),(5861,1073,'Issue',3,'Subject Tier 1 is course category. Subject Tier 2 is course name. Subject Tier 3 is unspecified','2013-05-01 11:41:27',0),(5862,1083,'Issue',21,'Hi Tracey, I think I\'ve finished working through your feedback.','2013-05-01 12:04:40',0),(5863,1080,'Issue',21,'','2013-05-01 14:51:11',0),(5864,1089,'Issue',6,'I assume date of birth should be before today and within the last 120 years.\r\nI assume warning means the new warning status (same as for postcode ZZ99 ZZZ).','2013-05-01 16:02:26',0),(5865,1090,'Issue',6,'I assume date of birth should be before today and within the last 120 years.\r\nI assume warning means the new warning status (same as for postcode ZZ99 ZZZ).','2013-05-01 16:02:27',0),(5866,1029,'Issue',6,NULL,'2013-05-01 16:03:20',0),(5867,1053,'Issue',6,NULL,'2013-05-01 16:03:21',0),(5868,1083,'Issue',6,'The code formatting is fine and the site appears to be secure, only a logged in user can list, edit or delete their books.\r\n\r\nYou have hardcoded the path in the before filter to \"/home/index.html\", this tries to redirect to \r\n\"www.terrabase.co.uk/home/index.html\" which doesn\'t exist. You should use home_index_path, which correctly redirects to \"www.terrabase.co.uk/purplestar/helloworld/home/index\".\r\n\r\nYou can run @rake routes@ to get a list of the available routes, append \"_path\" to any item in the first column.\r\nYou may wish to watch \"Railscast 203 Routing in Rails 3\":http://railscasts.com/episodes/203-routing-in-rails-3 or read the \"Rails Routing Guide\":http://guides.rubyonrails.org/routing.html\r\n\r\nThe sorting works, but I get an error in the firefox firebug console that the image cannot be found. Images should be in app/assets/images and you should use the image-url helper method to refer to them.\r\nSo instead of \r\n<pre>\r\nbackground-image: url(/images/up_arrow.gif);\r\n</pre>\r\nit should be \r\n<pre>\r\n@background-image: image-url(\'up_arrow.gif\');\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nThis uses the asset pipeline to add the correct path to the image taking into account where the application is deployed to. \r\nYou may wish to read the \"Asset pipeline guide\":http://guides.rubyonrails.org/asset_pipeline.html or watch the \"Railscast 279 Understanding the asset pipeline\":http://railscasts.com/episodes/279-understanding-the-asset-pipeline though this is probably a little out of date.\r\n\r\nThe Railscast you followed was made before Rails 3.1 was released which is when the asset pipeline was introduced.\r\n\r\nShouldn\'t the sorting be for issue #1078?\r\n\r\nCould you correct the redirect in the before filter, so that I can release it.','2013-05-01 18:31:11',0),(5869,1083,'Issue',21,'Hi Tracey, thanks for the feedback.\r\n\r\nI\'ve changed the before filter to use home_index_path as requested. Sorry I didn\'t spot this error - it works with /home/index.html on my setup.\r\n\r\nI\'ve changed the lines in app/assets/stylesheets/application.css to be\r\n@background-image: image-url(\'up_arrow.gif\');\r\netc. and I\'ve moved the images to app/assets/images but they now aren\'t showing up (they were displaying correctly for me when in public/images with the old code). I\'ve had a look at the Asset Pipeline guide, but I can\'t see what I\'m doing wrong.\r\n\r\nI zipped up the latest version of the app which includes the current column sorting code.\r\n\r\nI\'ve attached the current code. Thanks.','2013-05-02 16:27:17',0),(5870,1083,'Issue',21,'','2013-05-02 16:27:35',0),(5871,1083,'Issue',6,'The before filter is now working fine.\r\n\r\nThe image issue is partly a mis-type by me. It should be:\r\n<pre>\r\nbackground-image: image-url(\'up_arrow.gif\');\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nbut there is also another issue that the image-url method only works in scss files. \r\nThe application.css file is a manifest file and does not usually contain css rules.\r\nIf you move the css rules to one of the existing .css.scss files it should work.\r\n\r\nAt the moment the deployment is failing due to the extra @ in the css file.','2013-05-07 12:59:48',0),(5872,1083,'Issue',21,'','2013-05-07 15:23:21',0),(5873,1083,'Issue',21,'Thanks Tracey. I\'ve corrected the image code and moved the css rules to books.css.scss.','2013-05-08 10:54:42',0),(5874,1083,'Issue',6,'Deployed successfully.\r\n\r\nReleased to http://www.terrabase.co.uk/purplestar/helloworld','2013-05-08 12:35:08',0),(5875,1080,'Issue',3,'','2013-05-08 13:44:14',0),(5876,1083,'Issue',3,'Good stuff!','2013-05-08 13:46:32',0),(5877,1088,'Issue',3,NULL,'2013-05-08 15:36:40',0),(5878,1091,'Issue',3,NULL,'2013-05-08 15:36:49',0),(5879,1073,'Issue',3,NULL,'2013-05-08 15:37:33',0),(5880,1073,'Issue',6,'Released to edge\r\n\r\nThe Postcode, distance and map have not been implemented and are shown for layout purposes only. The Distance is hard-coded to 1 mile.\r\n\r\nVery few courses have a provider name as only a few have a project code that matches an Aqua project code in Aldas.\r\n\r\nIE10 works but does not show the background gradient correctly.\r\n\r\nThe overnight update is scheduled to run at 23:15 every day. You can check if it ran successfully by checking the last successful update date on the course search page when you are logged in as an admin.\r\n\r\nIf an update fails it will automatically email me a failure report and try again. \r\n\r\nThis cannot be released to live until I have the url and authentication details for the live AQUA web service. I will