hould work until the portal is next released. I will continue to investigate this intermittent issue to find a more permanent solution and will monitor the temporary fix.','2013-07-05 11:35:20',0),(6149,1125,'Issue',6,'Authentication\r\n(Assuming login to website)\r\nPasswords are stored as a salted hash.\r\nSSL is always a good idea for logins.\r\nSSL Cert from reputable provider, Don\'t see that it matters that much as long as its recognised by all browsers, it just probably costs more.\r\nPassword complexity could be added, but just means users forget passwords or write them on post-it notes.\r\nLogon restrictions, e.g. lock account for an hour after 3 failed logins, are a good idea and can be easily implemented with authlogic.\r\nDisabling or deleting test/guest accounts is a good idea.\r\nExpire inactive accounts probably something we should get clients to consider more, but not something we usually enforce. I leave it to admins to manually delete old unneeded accounts.\r\nPassword-less authentication never done it don\'t know what viable alternatives would be.\r\n\r\nServer\r\nPatching tends to be done manually the weekend after the monthly backup.\r\nSSH and mail are essential but the mail server only sends from itself.\r\nAs we only have one server it is not possible to separate the web front end from the db backend.\r\nFirewall limits incoming traffic.\r\nBackup procedures in place.\r\nFile integrity checker, don\'t really do this. Which files should be checked?\r\n\r\nWebsite\r\nCookies I normally just go with the rails defaults,\r\nXSS, SQL injection protection come by default in rails.\r\nMysql is only accessible by processes on the server no remote access.\r\nForm tampering - Rails provides protection to ensure the only fields updated from a posted form are those that are permitted. Sensitive fields may have added protection.\r\nError messages - Agree, validation errors should be meaningful, except when logging in never state whether it was username or password that failed. Other server issues just say \"We encountered an error\" without any details.\r\nReusing existing code - Yes I will tend to use gems (libraries) where possible e.g. authologic for authentication which handles the salting and hashing of password, login restrictions.\r\n\r\nMisc\r\nDDos - very vunerable, as we only have one server if all the users of all the applications tried to use the systems at once it would probably cause resource problems. \r\nDon\'t know if 1and1 have any protections.\r\n\r\nDeployed code is never in debug mode.\r\n\r\nI think the other issues are outside my area. \r\n','2013-07-05 12:09:56',0),(6150,1124,'Issue',6,'','2013-07-08 15:43:14',0),(6151,1125,'Issue',3,'Thanks','2013-07-09 10:03:54',0),(6152,1121,'Issue',3,'','2013-07-09 10:04:23',0),(6153,1125,'Issue',6,NULL,'2013-07-09 14:53:50',0),(6154,1121,'Issue',6,NULL,'2013-07-09 14:54:00',0),(6155,1114,'Issue',21,'','2013-07-10 12:35:27',0),(6156,1114,'Issue',6,'','2013-07-10 14:29:34',0),(6157,1124,'Issue',6,'Released to http://www.terrabase.co.uk/imperial_edge\r\n\r\nUsername: Admin\r\nPassword: n8b2x9a9\r\n\r\nThe Manage lookups drop-down has some entries, but they are just place-holders to show the styling, they will only work once the relevant lookup is added.\r\n\r\nStudents, Courses and Users links work but not as dialogs and without any styling/design. ','2013-07-10 18:18:50',0),(6158,1124,'Issue',3,'Love it! Works really well!\r\n\r\nJust a few cosmetics\r\n\r\n1. Try to get the fonts/font sizes to match the screen-shot more closely\r\n2. Mouse-over on links should not have black background. Perhaps highlight with Imperial Red (e41937) foreground text with no background colour\r\n3. I seemed to manage to kill it when I enetered \"Science, Culture and Society\" into the Fields of Study. Did the comma cause a problem, or I press <Return> rather than clicking OK? (i.e. Did not appear on the grid and click Add new item did not respond)\r\n4. Title \"Imperial Horizo