in the detail panel. If the course appears in the course list it will be highlighted, if the user scrolls down and the course is loaded into the list as part of the endless scroll it will now appear highlighted.\r\nAlso general improvements to students and courses so that if and when the selected detail record appears in the list it should always be highlighted.','2013-11-18 20:50:59',0),(6830,1064,'Issue',3,NULL,'2013-11-19 15:11:00',0),(6831,1202,'Issue',6,'Adding and saving a client gave an error at first, but I traced the problem to dodgy data. I had some assessments with client_id nil from early work on the assessments. Once I deleted the dodgy data things worked much better.\r\n\r\nSaving a new client with no data added, results in the ART Assessments header being added to the bottom of the form partly behind the footer.\r\n\r\nThe \"Invalid fields are marked in red\" covered by overlay so doesn\'t stand out.\r\n\r\nOrganisation name is correctly highlighted in red with an error message but is now shorter, the length should not change.\r\n\r\nSearch field doesn\'t work for assessed by or partner name.\r\n\r\nEditing an assessment doesn\'t work.\r\nif you change the edit action in the assessments_controller.rb from\r\n<pre>\r\n    @section = Section.where(position: params[:section]).first\r\n</pre>\r\nto\r\n<pre>\r\n    section_position = params[:section] || 1\r\n    @section = Section.where(position: section_position).first\r\n</pre>\r\nand add the dialog class to the edit link it should work.\r\n\r\n\r\nI have only tested in Firefox 25 on Kubuntu 12.04.\r\n\r\n*Code review*\r\n\r\n_assessments.html.erb\r\nWhy @Assessment.where(client_id: @client.id)@ when @@client.assessments@ is shorter and more readable?\r\n\r\nSimilarly @User.find(assessment.user_id).username@ could be @assessment.user.username@\r\nand Partner.find_by_id(User.find(assessment.user_id).id).try(:name) could be assessment.user.partner.try(:name)\r\n\r\n_form.html.erb\r\nYou don\'t need the @|| \'Name\'@ etc, that had been added in Imperial as several fields did not have a label, the specification has now been changed to add labels and the @|| \'Name\'@ etc has been removed.\r\n\r\n_clients.html.erb\r\n\r\nwhy are you not using the client_item helper.\r\n\r\n@client.contact_name != \'\'@ could be @client.contact_name.present?@\r\n\r\nlist_dialog.js.coffee\r\n\r\nyou are doing css in javascript again.\r\n\r\napp/views/pages/home.html.erb\r\nThe assessments count should only include assessments for clients that have not been deleted.\r\nProbably worth adding a scope to assessment.\r\n\r\nroutes.rb\r\nwhy are there two @resources :clients@ ?\r\n\r\n*General*\r\n\r\nYou have @Client.where(deleted: false)@ in many places. If the definition of visible clients changes again all the places will need to be updated, if you had used a scope it would only have needed to be changed in one place.\r\n\r\n@scope :active, lambda { where(deleted: false) }@\r\nthen @Client.active.count@ etc.\r\n\r\n\r\n*Automated testing*\r\n\r\nTests all passed.\r\n\r\nclients_spec.rb\r\nwhy do you have the @wait()@ in most of the tests? All the tests pass without it.\r\n\r\n\r\n*Quick-filter*\r\n\r\nThe categories method needs to return 3 things for the specified category.\r\ndata - the collection of items that should appear in the data drop-down e.g. @User.joins(:assessments).uniq@\r\nlookup_id - is the method that can be called on data to return the value. e.g. @\'id\'@\r\nlookup_name - is the method that can be called on data to return the text that actually appears in the dropdown. e.g. @\'username\'@\r\n\r\nThese values are used by the quick-filter helper (in application_helper.rb) as parameters for options_from_collection_for_select.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe create_filter method returns an array, for the specified category, that is turned into values for ransack by the search method (filter_base.rb)\r\nThe first item in the array should be the field is used for the comparison. e.g. @\'assessment_user_id\'@,\r\nthe second item is the comparison operator, e.g. @\'eq\'@ for equals,\r\nthe last item is a modifier if the field is boolean it should be @\'null\'@ otherwise it is probably @\'blank\'@. It\'s used when the data value is blank.\r\n\r\nLet me know if you are still having problems with the quick-filter\r\n','2013-11-19 18:57:57',0),(6832,1197,'Issue',6,'Released to edge\r\n\r\nCourse management complete see previous comment for details.\r\n\r\nStudents\r\n3.30 Enter mark Dialogue complete.\r\nI could not find details of the the mapping of percentage or A,B,C,D,E to Distinction, Pass and Failure so have guessed the following values:\r\nDistinction - A, 81-100\r\nPass - B,C, 51-80\r\nFailure - D,E, 0-50\r\nThese values can easily be changed if incorrect.\r\n\r\nCredit link now appears and toggles. I have moved it down a line as it wouldn\'t fit on the top line with the long course titles.\r\nCredit has been added to the quick-filter.\r\n\r\nThe status category in the quick-filter now actually works.\r\n\r\nWithdraw now allows reason to be entered and if not blank its appended to the student notes with the following header \"Withdrawn from [CourseName]:[GroupName] on [WithdrawalDate]\"\r\n\r\nAdmin Swtichboard\r\nThe statistics section now matches the specification with totals for the separate years.\r\n\r\n\r\nImport Attendance\r\nThe link now works, the unmatched barcode dialogue has not been implemented yet as it is not actually in the specification. Spreadsheets (.xls and .xlsx) can be imported and if accepted will create/update attendance records.\r\nStudents in the group whose library code is not in the spreadsheet will be marked as absent (O).\r\nWithdrawn students will not be marked as absent, though will be marked as present if their library code is included.\r\n\r\nThe Export data, and Email selection links have still to be implemented.\r\nThe counts on students and courses have also not yet been implemented as I worked against version 1.2.4 which does not show the counts. They will be included in the next release.\r\n\r\nI have imported the two spreadsheets (FirstYears.xlsx and Horizons second year cid lib number.xlsx attached to email \"library barcodes file\" dated 01/11/2013) into edge. These map the CID to the library code. There are 652 students without a library code in edge. I will import these files into live as part of the release to live.\r\n\r\n','2013-11-24 21:07:15',0),(6833,1202,'Issue',6,'Sorry Sophie, I have not had chance to review and merge the changes as I had hoped, carry on working, push you changes again before you finish and I will try to do the merge on Monday after you have finished for the day, now the Imperial release is finally done. ','2013-11-24 21:26:25',0),(6834,1197,'Issue',3,'Looks really good. Thanks!\r\n\r\nPlease do an interim release and return the issue back down to original priority.\r\n\r\nI have put an updated spec which includes the updated data imported dialogue (p12-13) spec 1.2.6\r\n\r\nI shall speak with Imperial about your other questions and further update the spec.\r\n\r\n','2013-11-25 14:46:18',0),(6835,1202,'Issue',6,'I have rebased the client_management_2 branch onto master, then rebased client_management_3 onto the new master.\r\n\r\nThere were a lot of merge conflicts, so I have had to manually merge in some places, I think I have all your changes included but I had to make some changes to allow both branches to work.\r\n\r\nThe above has fixed the issue that was in client_management_2 for IE7 not showing the add or close icons.\r\n\r\nI have also added a change to allow a user with a partner role to manage the client management and the assessments.\r\n\r\nI had to remove a position: relative from the add and edit links in the assessment list as it was preventing IE7 from scrolling correctly.\r\n\r\nThe Save and Cancel when adding/editing appear a little to high, but I will leave that to you to fix as you need to add icons anyway.\r\n\r\nWhen editing a client with a lot of assessments the list goes off the bottom but is hidden behind the footer so you can\'t actually see the bottom of the list.\r\n\r\nThe add/edit form does not appear correctly in IE7.\r\n\r\nThe postal address also seems a little taller than in the specification.\r\n\r\nThe \"upload organisation logo\" and \"No ART Assessments have been carried out yet\" do not appear correctly in IE8 and IE7 the drop shadow covers the whole background, the solution is to add a white background.\r\n\r\nI have also traced the last issue you had \"can\'t convert nil into String app/helpers/clients_helper.rb:61:in `+\'\". This is not actually due to the partner sort, I think sorting by partner just brought a client with no contact_name into the list. The problem is that a contact_name may be nil rather than an empty string, you then try to add a string to nil using + which gives the error. \r\nThe fix is to either call to_s on the contact_name to explicitly convert it into a string, or better still to use string interpolation, which is more efficient than adding strings together. \r\nI have implemented this second fix (string interpolation) so I could test.\r\n\r\nThe changes are all in master so could you start a new branch from master.','2013-11-25 21:08:36',0),(6836,1202,'Issue',6,'','2013-11-26 15:07:56',0),(6837,1233,'Issue',3,NULL,'2013-11-26 15:25:43',0),(6838,1229,'Issue',3,NULL,'2013-11-26 15:27:35',0),(6839,1233,'Issue',3,NULL,'2013-11-26 15:27:48',0),(6840,1185,'Issue',3,NULL,'2013-11-26 15:37:34',0),(6841,1233,'Issue',3,NULL,'2013-11-26 15:37:48',0),(6842,1229,'Issue',3,NULL,'2013-11-26 15:37:58',0),(6843,1197,'Issue',6,'Released approved interim version to live.\r\n\r\nI have imported the two spreadsheets (FirstYears.xlsx and Horizons second year cid lib number.xlsx attached to email \"library barcodes file\" dated 01/11/2013) into live.\r\nThere are 653 students without a library code.\r\n\r\nI have not imported any attendance data, as the users can now do the imports.','2013-11-28 19:52:34',0),(6844,1197,'Issue',6,'Released to edge\r\n\r\nAdded feedback \"Updating register...\" when Accept button is clicked on the import attendance data, it appears with the same gif and font as the \"Uploading and Importing...\" feedback.\r\n\r\nAdded the unmatched barcodes list as shown in the revised specification (version 1.2.6).\r\n\r\nAdded the number of records in filter and number of records in system to the student and courses dialogues. \r\nThe filter count will only include records a lecturer has access to, the total count includes all students/courses in the system whether the lecturer has access or not. Is this correct or should the total for lecturers be the total records they have access to?\r\n\r\nAdded Export Data link and dialogue as described in the revised specification.\r\n\r\nWhilst browser compatibility testing the above changes I noticed a problem with the attendance upload, in IE the buttons and drop-downs are still active when uploading. This has now been fixed.\r\n\r\nWhilst testing the fix I discovered a problem if you upload a none xls,xlsx file, an error appears saying its an invalid type, but the \"Uploading and importing..\" text is shown and the \"Upload and Import\" button remains disabled even after selecting a correct file. This has now been fixed.\r\n\r\nFurther testing showed there is also a problem if the spreadsheet is completely blank. This has also now been fixed.\r\nA temporary workaround if these problems, except the blank spreadsheet, are encountered in live is to close the dialogue or refresh the page.\r\n\r\nA blank spreadsheet will now show an attendance percentage of zero with the associated message recommending the user to Reject the upload, however if they accept it will mark all the student in the class as absent \'O\' as their barcodes are not included in the file.\r\n\r\nI believe Phase 2 is now complete except for the Email selection on Students, as I am waiting for a re