INSERT INTO `journals` VALUES (6924,1202,'Issue',6,'I have added the scope for assessments to only include active clients.\r\n\r\nI have also fixed the assessed by and partner name sorting, As I thought it should sort by the latest assessment details only. I have added last_assessment_id to client and a has_one association between assessment and client. I then amended the sort to use the last_assessment association. Tony said the quick-filter and search using all assessments was correct.\r\n\r\nI amended the assessment creation to update the last_assessment_id.\r\nYou can use @Client.all.each {|c| c.reset_last_assessment}@ in the rails console to update existing clients with the last_assessment_id.\r\n\r\nI have also implemented deleting assessments and reset the last_assessment_id if the last assessment is deleted.\r\n\r\nTony changed the specification again after I pointed out the old specification showed the prev/next links as active. As it was only a small change I have implemented that, and also greyed out the edit and delete link so it is more obvious to the user the links are disabled.\r\nThe toolkit and report icons will also need greyed out versions but I have left that for later.\r\n\r\nI also added a small improvement to the assessment general details so the dialog is the same size as the rest of the questionnaire.\r\n\r\nI also had to update selenium-webdriver to be compatible with Firefox 26.\r\n\r\nI have also updated rails to 3.2.16 so please bundle and run rake db:migrate after pulling these changes.\r\n\r\nI have also noticed that the clients close button reloads the page instead of just closing the dialog, I am sure you fixed this in the past, so I have fixed it.\r\n\r\nThe client management and referral management have been released to edge for Tony to check.','2013-12-18 20:47:23',0),(6925,1198,'Issue',6,'Released interim version to edge\r\n\r\nClient management is implemented except the logo, the date range in the quick-filter, the toolkit and report links in the assessment list, and the refer to a partner organisation link. Referrals are also not shown as the answers are still not being saved.\r\n\r\nReferral management is fully implemented.\r\n\r\nThe Questionnaire now has a scroll bar on the general details page, and the questions numbers now appear as 2.04 rather than 2.4 to be consistent with the Referral management which needs that format to sort alphanumerically rather than alphabetically. Let me know if this is a problem.\r\n\r\nThe client and assessment counts on the switchboard only include non-deleted clients.\r\n\r\nPlease note that the partner name searching, sorting and quick-filter will only work if a partner user has done an assessment, or for sorting did the last assessment. An admin user does not have an associated partner so the partner details will be blank if an admin user created the assessment.','2013-12-18 21:10:03',0),(6926,1237,'Issue',6,'Released to Coventry edge','2013-12-18 21:32:05',0),(6927,1241,'Issue',6,'Released to Coventry edge\r\n\r\nAll the unused fields have been deleted from enrolment mappings unless they were linked to an advanced filter or added manually after the initial setup.','2013-12-18 21:35:55',0),(6928,1185,'Issue',3,'','2013-12-19 11:06:57',0),(6929,1198,'Issue',3,'Really good. Responsive and has a quality feel about it.\r\n\r\nMarked as Not Approved as this is an interim release.\r\n\r\nNumbers on the first page (General) need to follow the 1.01, 1.02 etc convention\r\n\r\nFor sorting on Partner, if no assessment done is it assumed the partner etc are blank?','2013-12-19 11:27:49',0),(6930,1241,'Issue',3,'','2013-12-19 11:38:23',0),(6931,1202,'Issue',21,'','2013-12-19 11:40:13',0),(6932,1234,'Issue',21,'','2013-12-19 11:42:38',0),(6933,1198,'Issue',3,'Spec version 1.3.4 released to share','2013-12-19 16:36:33',0),(6934,1185,'Issue',6,NULL,'2013-12-19 17:20:54',0),(6935,1198,'Issue',6,'Yes if there is no assessment the partner and assessed by are treated as