rite these fixes. Copy the current text to replace the contents of the body tags in your editor, when you update the text in the future please only add the contents of the body tags not the doctype, html, head or body tags as these are only allowed once per page.\r\n\r\nI will keep a copy of my fixed code just in case.\r\n','2014-02-11 21:07:54',0),(7077,1257,'Issue',3,'11.25 hours. Yikes!','2014-02-12 10:11:53',0),(7078,1242,'Issue',21,'','2014-02-13 10:20:35',0),(7079,1263,'Issue',3,'\"As for the rate column, this would be the % of enrolments who were on the lowest level in the earliest year.  So in the 11/12 – 12/13 boxes in the table above the enrols would be the number of enrolments who were on Entry 1 in 11/12 who had gone on to Entry 2 in 12/13 eg 10 and the rate would be what percentage this number was of the total number of enrolments studying at Entry 1 in 11/12 so if there were 100 enrolments in 11/12 who were 19+ and studying Entry 1 then the 10 who had moved onto Entry 2 would be 10% and this is the rate that goes in the table.\"','2014-02-14 15:08:36',0),(7080,1257,'Issue',6,NULL,'2014-02-14 16:09:01',0),(7081,1263,'Issue',3,'','2014-02-17 10:26:43',0),(7082,1265,'Issue',6,'','2014-02-17 15:24:02',0),(7083,1242,'Issue',21,'Hi Tracey,\r\n\r\nI\'ve pushed the current code for review. The remaining issues are:\r\n\r\n- datepicker icon positioning in IE/Safari/Chrome\r\n- blue bars appearing white in IE9\r\n- form alignment incorrect in IE7\r\n- text in resources list needs truncating as mentioned in spec.\r\n\r\nThanks\r\n','2014-02-17 16:33:43',0),(7084,1265,'Issue',6,'Released to edge\r\n\r\nLecturers have access to the report page but just have a message \"You have no reports available\", this is a temporary message that can be removed once lecturers have access to a report. (A blank dialogue may have been mistaken for an error.)\r\n\r\nAdmins have the 2 SOLE reports, all fields must have a value entered/selected before the Generate button is activated. Once Generate is clicked a message \"Generating report...\" is shown and the fields and buttons are disabled, like on the export. The xls is generated in the background and will automatically be downloaded/opened the same as the export.\r\n\r\nThe xls files have the same headers/columns as the first sheet in the attached examples.\r\n\r\nLecturers will appear more than once if they have more than one group with classes in the date range associated with the period code.\r\n\r\nStudents will only appear once and will show the course with the most recent class in the date range associated with the period code.\r\n\r\nIf there are no classes in the period then an xls with just the relevant header row will be created.','2014-02-18 22:05:21',0),(7085,1265,'Issue',3,'Some notes from Imperial:\r\n\r\n1. Is the Period Code always in the same format?\r\n\r\ni.e. TTT-Hyy\r\n\r\nwhere TTT is the term (AUT, SPR, SUM), H is \'H\' and yy is the year. So, this term would be SPR-H14\r\n\r\nThe answer to 1 is yes (we only do two surveys though (AUT & SPR)\r\n\r\n2. We are filtering the results by term, so the user selects the term (up to 10 years back in time when we have the data), and the export is created. Is this correct?\r\n\r\nWe will only need it for the current students really.  ICT need as list of all the students detailing which course they are on and then when the student logs in to the SOLE survey they only see the specific courses (with the correct staff) that they are taking.  \r\n\r\n3. Is the lecturer export always per term too?\r\n\r\nYes\r\n\r\n4. Does a course count for a particular term if its start date or finish date is in that term (i.e. students whose course begins in AUT and ends in SPR would appear in both the AUT export and the SPR export)?\r\n\r\nYes.  So the language courses that last for the 2 terms are asked for their comments about the same course and same lecturer twice.\r\n\r\n\r\nCan you make the dropdown only go 2 years back in time and exclude the SUM options.\r\n\r\nThe generate link is not being coloured blue when all the data is entered, although it does work.\r\n','2014-02-19 10:22:18',0),(7086,1250,'Issue',21,'','2014-02-19 16:26:39',0),(7087,1265,'Issue',6,'Released to edge\r\n\r\nAmended period code drop-down to be 2 years and removed summer, date ranges unchanged so students/lecturers for classes between Easter and 31 July will never be included.\r\n\r\nGenerate link should be enabled as soon as a character is entered in all fields','2014-02-19 16:44:32',0),(7088,1265,'Issue',3,'','2014-02-19 16:45:43',0),(7089,1250,'Issue',6,'The description only stores 255 characters but the specification says up to 65000 should be allowed. No validation error is given, the entered text is just truncated.\r\n\r\nWhy when editing a referral are there 2 ajax requests to get the question and answer texts, can\'t they just be shown in the form if its not a new record?\r\n\r\nWhy do you need the question_info and action_info actions? can\'t the text be extracted from the selected option title using javascript?\r\n\r\nIf a user enters more than 65000 characters, when creating a referral, the error message shows correctly but any selected answer is lost as the answer drop-down only has the Unselected option, the Question text is shown but again the answer text is not shown (suggest temporarily changing the maximum length validation to a lower figure for debugging)\r\nIt works correctly if an existing referral is edited.\r\n\r\nThere don\'t appear to be any checks in the tests to see if the question and answer texts are shown.\r\n\r\nIn the referrals_controller data_field action \r\n<pre>\r\n  def data_field\r\n    if Question.where(:id => params[:category])\r\n      q = Question.find(params[:category])\r\n      @settings = [[\"Unselected\", \"\"], [\"1\", \"1\", title: q.answer_1_text], [\"2\", \"2\", title: q.answer_2_text], [\"3\", \"3\",   end\r\ntitle:q.answer_3_text], [\"4\", \"4\", title:q.answer_4_text]]\r\n    else\r\n      @settings = []\r\n    end\r\n  end\r\n</pre>\r\nwhy do you get the question from the database twice? why not\r\n<pre>\r\n  def data_field\r\n    q = Question.find_by_id(params[:category])\r\n    if q\r\n      @settings = [[\"Unselected\", \"\"], [\"1\", \"1\", title: q.answer_1_text], [\"2\", \"2\", title: q.answer_2_text], [\"3\", \"3\",   \r\ntitle:q.answer_3_text], [\"4\", \"4\", title:q.answer_4_text]]\r\n    else\r\n      @settings = []\r\n    end\r\n  end\r\n</pre>\r\nalso why :category and @settings wouldn\'t :question_id and @answers make more sense?\r\n\r\nThe array is also repeated in the form partial, wouldn\'t it be more DRY to extract it into a helper passing the question as a parameter?','2014-02-19 18:58:26',0),(7090,1265,'Issue',6,'Released to live','2014-02-19 21:01:40',0),(7091,1267,'Issue',3,'','2014-02-20 10:45:57',0),(7092,1250,'Issue',21,'','2014-02-20 12:20:38',0),(7093,1268,'Issue',6,'Not sure a blank space will work, how will the lecturer know where to click to change it to X, or will they first use change all to X, then update the absent students.','2014-02-20 15:22:46',0),(7094,1267,'Issue',6,'Data updated in live to set the withdrawn flag to false and the withdrawal date to null for all 4 students. The notes have not been updated.\r\n\r\nThe next time the registers for those groups are opened, the students will be marked with X for any missing classes.','2014-02-20 15:53:34',0),(7095,1263,'Issue',6,'','2014-02-20 20:49:26',0),(7096,1269,'Issue',6,'Released to edge.\r\n\r\nIf a student withdrew from a course and enrolled on another they will be shown with the new course details.\r\n\r\nIf a student withdrew and is not on any other courses they will be excluded from the report.','2014-02-21 12:29:41',0),(7097,1269,'Issue',3,'','2014-02-21 13:47:33',0),(7098,1269,'Issue',6,'Released to live','2014-02-21 13:58:58',0),(7099,1267,'Issue',3,'','2014-02-24 15:00:28',0),(7100,1267,'Issue',6,NULL,'2014-02-24 15:12:11',0),(7101,1250,'Is