rectly. These are now fixed, I believe.\r\n\r\nThe tests currently use several wait() statements as many test fail intermittently on my machine if I don\'t include this.\r\n\r\nCould you let me know if I\'m on the right track?\r\n\r\nThanks\r\n\r\n','2014-02-27 15:05:49',0),(7105,1251,'Issue',21,'','2014-02-27 17:41:52',0),(7106,1250,'Issue',6,'I had one test failure related to referrals\r\n./spec/features/referrals_spec.rb:281 # Referrals POST /referrals OK button should be enabled when all data entered\r\n\r\nDoing the same actions manually in the browser worked fine. I think the failure is a timing issue as adding a sleep 1 after the wait fixed it, not liking that solution I amended to line checking if the button is disabled to use the same code as I had used in Imperial attendance uploads.\r\nSo on line 298 I changed\r\n<pre>\r\n  find(\"#referral-submit\")[\'disabled\'].should eq nil\r\n</pre>\r\nto be \r\n<pre>\r\n  expect(find_button(\'referral-submit\')[\'disabled\']).to be_false\r\n</pre>\r\nThis works without the sleep 1 or wait, but I think the wait can be left in to ensure it works for you.\r\n\r\nThe tests you added look fine, you seem to have covered all the behaviour.\r\n\r\nI have tested in all required browsers and, apart from the issue with the tool-tips not showing in Safari, everything worked perfectly. The Safari issue appears to be that Safari have not implemented the tool-tips for the title attribute on the option element in a select.\r\n\r\nIf you make that change to the test, and release for approval, I will approve this issue, though as its branched from a part working resource management I won\'t be able to merge it into master or release it until the Resources management is finished.','2014-02-27 18:38:45',0),(7107,1242,'Issue',6,'Sorry for the delay reviewing this.\r\n\r\n- datepicker icon positioning in IE/Safari/Chrome\r\nin resources.css.scss\r\n.resources-panel .detail_col #resource-detail div.field table.resource_form .ui-date-picke