 are 8 classes or less they will not scroll and will be evenly spread across the width of the scroll area, over 8 classes will enable scrolling. I have tested with 41 classes which should be around the maximum.\r\n\r\nFixed issue with IE9 intermittently creating a phantom cell causing one row to be wider than the others and thus not lining up with the header and footer. This may be happening in live if there are a lot of classes.\r\n\r\nFinally fixed all browser compatibility issues with Chrome, Safari and IE.\r\n\r\nTested in IE11 and fixed an issue where the green gradient on the student and courses did not appear.\r\n\r\nI think the problem with IE7 with a lot (230) of students may be fixed by the above changes, but I have not extensively tested it as we agreed IE7 would no longer be supported.\r\n\r\nAdded Department name between degree code and faculty name in the main export.\r\n\r\nI have also amended the library code import for the latest spreadsheet format and imported the 10 library codes in the spreadsheet in to edge. \r\n\r\nNo data has been fixed or imported in live, I will do that once these changes are approved and released to live.\r\n\r\n*Testing Advice*\r\n\r\nSort the students on Date descending to see the students with photos.\r\n\r\nThe \"Introduction to business\" course has several students with images.','2014-03-26 22:19:27',0),(7168,1274,'Issue',6,'Released to Coventry Live\r\n\r\nThere are no failed progression reports to reset, they must have been for quick-filters.','2014-03-26 22:30:41',0),(7169,1266,'Issue',3,'','2014-03-27 11:13:07',0),(7170,1273,'Issue',3,NULL,'2014-03-27 15:01:54',0),(7171,1273,'Issue',6,'eSubmissionRTI.dll is in Dropbox.\r\n\r\nThe SSPYTD field on Payment has been removed.\r\n\r\nAn optional LateReason field has been added to Payment. Acceptable values with meanings:\r\nA: Notional payment: Payment to Expat by third party or overseas employer\r\nB: Notional payment: Employment related security\r\nC: Notional payment