sed postcode\" in amber next to the postcode on the details, could not be implemented as the postcode is not actually shown in the details.\r\n\r\nThe outstanding development items are:\r\n1. Resource management/Suggested Toolkit - Previews \r\n2. Questionnaire - Logic Notifiers \r\n3. Outcome Report, and Email Outcome Report - awaiting actual format of report.\r\n4. Updating questions whilst keeping the full history intact.\r\n\r\nI believe everything else is either coded or no longer required.\r\n\r\nPlease raise issues for these outstanding items if they are still required as I intend to close this issue once approved and released to live.','2014-06-17 19:33:52',0),(7273,1198,'Issue',3,'','2014-06-18 14:33:00',0),(7274,1293,'Issue',6,'Released to edge','2014-06-18 15:57:00',0),(7275,1282,'Issue',3,'I was going to send an email to Coventry stating:\r\n\r\n\"From the data we have there are the following values E, EL1, EL2, EL3, 01, 02, 03, 04, 05, 06, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, NK in the spreadsheet, but as you can see the figures spot no progression in the entry levels and fairly limited progression in the other levels. Is there anything else you would normally do to increase the figures, or are these around what you would expect?\"\r\n\r\nDoes this sound reasonable? Any other reasons the figures (particularly for Entry level) are so low?','2014-06-18 16:33:06',0),(7276,1282,'Issue',6,'I have checked the level of learning on the 3130 courses for analysis 2011-2014 Progression (Edge).\r\n\r\n\"E\" = 852 courses\r\n\"1\" = 84 courses\r\n\"2\" = 94 courses\r\n\"02\" = 111 courses\r\n\"3\" = 32 courses\r\n\"6\" = 1957 courses\r\n\r\nSo I would expect the entry levels to show no progression and the other levels to show very little progression.\r\n\r\nDid you check the 3 imports for errors I am seeing a lot rejections for invalid level of learning. \r\nIt would probably help if the Aid file was amended to allow the new level of learnings.','2014-06-18 17:07:49',0),(7277,1198,'Is