thing is uploaded and the import is in the queue at that point. This was suggested in issue #883.\r\n\r\nIf the transfer of data from AQUA fails the status will show \"Transfer from AQUA failed\" and I will be emailed. There will also be one error in the import errors that should have a reason for the failure though it may not be very user friendly.\r\n\r\nThe new \"Download spreadsheet\" option will not be available until the transfer from AQUA is complete. This may take 5 minutes or more depending on the number of enrolments to be added to the spreadsheet. Uploaded spreadsheets will be available instantly and will be available for existing imports.','2014-06-25 19:56:44',0),(7287,1294,'Issue',6,'Released to edge\r\n\r\nI have amended the default link colour so that you no longer require the class \"_link2\" and all future links should just work.\r\nThe colour will be the same as for _link2, when hovering it will change to black and after being clicked will revert to its original colour not white thus disappearing. This also fixes the email link on the Privacy policy page.','2014-06-26 15:31:53',0),(7288,1289,'Issue',3,'Not sure if it\'s me.\r\nI have imported to analysis \'AQUA 170413 Investigation\' and downloaded the \'in-situ\' spreadsheet aqua-135.xls\r\n\r\nThere are lots of Special Rule errors for GLH import. Looking at, for example, row 77, the start date (column 58)  is 16/09/2013 and the end date (column 60) is 14/10/2013. The GLH (column 60) is 10 so should be acceptable as the max hours per day is set to 8.\r\n\r\nHere is the key from the aid file:\r\n\r\n<Field>tblCourse.GLHImport\r\n	<ALDASTableName>tblCourse</ALDASTableName>\r\n	<ALDASFieldName>GLHImport</ALDASFieldName>\r\n	<ExportFieldName>GLH</ExportFieldName>\r\n	<ColumnPosition>62</ColumnPosition>\r\n	<FieldType>text</FieldType>\r\n	<SpecialRule>Rule 4. Parameters(58,60,8,77)</SpecialRule>\r\n</Field>\r\n\r\nCan you see what\'s going wrong?\r\n\r\n','2014-06-26 17:24:04',0),(7289,1289,'Issue',6,'Released to Cheshire edge.\r\n\r\nIt wasn\'t you, there was a bug. The dates come through from AQUA as a date and time, if the date is in BST the time part was 23:00. The spreadsheet reading library converted this to a DateTime Class instead of the Date class used if the time was midnight. The import process was not expecting a DateTime class so set the date to nil, this meant the start and finish dates were sometimes nil.\r\n\r\nI have amended the AQUA transfer to convert all the dates to just a date, I have also amended the import process so that if it receives a DateTime class for a date it will convert the DateTime into a date.\r\n\r\nI have done a test import using the aidfile you were testing and there were only a few GLH Import errors, though still lots of level of learning errors. \r\n\r\nI also noticed that the venue does not have a unique field so a venue record is created for every row.','2014-06-26 21:06:16',0),(7290,1294,'Issue',3,'','2014-06-27 11:42:20',0),(7291,1289,'Issue',3,'','2014-06-27 13:43:17',0),(7292,1295,'Issue',6,'','2014-06-27 17:18:26',0),(7293,1296,'Issue',6,'','2014-06-27 17:18:50',0),(7294,1289,'Issue',6,'Released to Cheshire live.','2014-06-29 19:34:57',0),(7295,1294,'Issue',6,'Released to live','2014-06-29 19:40:17',0),(7296,1295,'Issue',6,'Released to edge\r\n\r\n\"Make sure (i) button does not move to line below on its own - always group with the last word if poss\" - Sorry, this was not possible.\r\n\r\nAll other items have been amended.','2014-06-30 18:36:46',0),(7297,1296,'Issue',6,'Released to edge\r\n\r\nAll changes implemented.\r\n\r\nSection data updated.','2014-06-30 18:39:51',0),(7298,1295,'Issue',3,'Looks good.\r\n\r\nI don\'t seem to be able to get resources to appear in my toolkit when I do an assessment. Maybe we can go through it on the phone next time.\r\n\r\nAlso, we\'ll have to do something about the assessment closing when you close the toolkit etc','2014-07-01 11:57:56',0),(7299,1296,'Issue',3,'','2014-07-01 12