aced them with \"Importing students...\", the title is also changed to \"Importing Student Data\". Once imported the final dialogue is shown as per the specification.\r\n\r\nIf the student cannot be saved due to validation errors not mentioned in the import specification but applied when adding/editing a student the errors will be shown in the log along with \"This record [will not be/has not been] imported.\"\r\n\r\nIf the student is already enrolled in the group then the student group record will be updated instead of created.\r\n\r\nIf the checking or importing fail I will be sent an email and the user will see \"Sorry an unexpected error was encountered.\" in large red font in the dialogue, there will also be a close button at the bottom right.\r\n\r\nIf they try to import a spreadsheet with no data or just the headers, the log will show \"No students to import\".\r\nOnly the first sheet will be imported.\r\n\r\nThere should be no problem with importing the same spreadsheet multiple times.\r\n\r\nIt would be a good idea to test with a spreadsheet from Imperial if you can obtain one.\r\n\r\nI have also fixed the issue with the course classes showing classes from other years or failing completely if there are no groups in the current academic year, but there are classes for other years.\r\n\r\n','2014-09-18 00:52:05',0),(7442,1305,'Issue',3,'','2014-09-19 12:34:30',0),(7443,1319,'Issue',3,NULL,'2014-09-19 12:35:08',0),(7444,1319,'Issue',6,'Assume this means pages 26 to 31 of Imperial Horizons Management System - 2014 Phase 3 - Report builder and general enhancements - Pt 1 - v1.0.0.pdf.','2014-09-19 15:17:49',0),(7445,1319,'Issue',3,NULL,'2014-09-19 15:47:27',0),(7446,1305,'Issue',3,NULL,'2014-09-19 15:47:47',0),(7447,1307,'Issue',3,'','2014-09-19 15:48:48',0),(7448,1319,'Issue',3,'1. Get the register looking the same as the very on the spec, with working LfS, YiE, C and NC icons, ticks rather than crosses etc and colours for absence etc\r\n2. Implement the email 