,'Issue',3,'Excellent, thanks Tracey.','2014-10-01 21:37:13',0),(7483,1326,'Issue',6,'Released to live','2014-10-01 21:51:15',0),(7484,1324,'Issue',3,'','2014-10-02 15:06:51',0),(7485,1324,'Issue',6,'Also undo withdrawal','2014-10-02 20:08:10',0),(7486,1324,'Issue',3,NULL,'2014-10-06 15:42:15',0),(7487,1327,'Issue',3,'In dropbox share','2014-10-06 15:43:58',0),(7488,1327,'Issue',6,NULL,'2014-10-06 16:34:22',0),(7489,1324,'Issue',6,'Released interim version to edge\r\n\r\nUndo withdrawal is not implemented.\r\n\r\nEmail from template is not implemented as no templates have been provided.\r\n\r\nAll existing groups have been set to be Standard.\r\n\r\nAll existing withdrawals will be treated as withdrawal rather than non-completer.\r\n\r\nAll existing students have post-grad and staff set to false.','2014-10-06 16:44:14',0),(7490,1324,'Issue',6,'Released another interim version to edge\r\n\r\nThis includes undo withdrawal.\r\n\r\nEmail from template is still not implemented as I am still waiting for templates to be provided.','2014-10-06 21:22:53',0),(7491,1324,'Issue',3,'Undo withdraw works but it seems to have broken the withdraw function. When you try to withdraw a student the withdraw dialogue keeps popping up again.','2014-10-07 14:50:26',0),(7492,1324,'Issue',3,'...also, can you put the Year End Posting link on the bottom right about two lines below where the grey boxes finish and right aligned to the Log out link','2014-10-07 14:52:18',0),(7493,1324,'Issue',6,'Released interim version to edge\r\n\r\nFixed withdrawal with blank reason keep popping up. Not actually caused by the undo withdrawal but by a bug fix released at the same time. It was adding the \"Withdrawn from [course]:[group] on [date] [reason]\" text to the student notes even if the date was invalid. I fixed this but forgot to test with a blank reason. Regression tests have been added.\r\n\r\nMoved year end posting link.\r\n\r\nEmail from template is still not released as I am still waiting for templates to be provided.','2014-10-07 20:29:37',0),(7494,1324,'Issue',3,'Looks great. Please release and return this issue to me for approval with a note that we are awaiting templates from Imperial.','2014-10-08 11:11:14',0),(7495,1305,'Issue',3,NULL,'2014-10-08 16:02:58',0),(7496,1324,'Issue',6,'Released to live\r\n\r\nThis release includes:\r\n* post-grad and staff check-boxes\r\n* ghost classes\r\n* library code import\r\n* pre-course withdrawal and non-completers\r\n* undo withdraw \r\n* year end link.\r\n\r\nEmail from template is implemented but still not released as I am still waiting for the templates to be provided.\r\n\r\nEmail from template will only enable the template drop-down if the body textarea is empty, to prevent accidental loss of data. \r\n\r\nThere is a minor problem with the re-enabling in IE9. The \'delete\' option on the right click menu does not fire an event that can be handled in javascript. There is nothing I can do to fix this except to advise use of a modern standards compliant browser as it works in the other browsers that provide a delete option. The \'cut\' option works correctly. The workaround to enable the template drop-down is to type a character in the body textarea then delete it.\r\n\r\nThe styling of the form has been amended slightly to allow more room for the template drop-down, and now more closely resembles the specification.\r\n\r\nThe email changes apply to both emailing from the register and the student list.\r\n\r\nI think I may also have fixed the \"Students pop-up to appear in middle of screen like dashboard pop-up\" problem in #1315. The register kept appearing low down and I kept having to scroll to see it, so I looked into the problem. Though you will have to wait for the email template release before testing.\r\n','2014-10-08 22:44:24',0),(7497,1328,'Issue',6,NULL,'2014-10-09 16:22:39',0),(7498,1327,'Issue',6,'Are any fields required, the only validations I can see are maximum length?\r\n\r\nPage 12 Whats the Referral ID?\r\n\r\nPage 16\r\nHow many login attempts should a user be allowed? \r\nShould the user be locked permanently or for a period of time? \r\nIf permanently, how are they unlocked?\r\nIf for a period of time, how long?\r\n\r\nI assume the practice and doctors list will be imported from a spreadsheet behind the scenes and then will be maintained behind the scenes.\r\n\r\nHow are users maintained, will that also be behind the scenes?\r\n\r\nWill there just be one user per practice or could there be several?\r\n\r\nPage 18 4 Installation\r\n\r\n1. Going to www.[GPSecureURL] and clicking on the \'Put an icon on my desktop link\'.\r\nDon\'t think this is possible. You can just drag the icon in/next to the address bar to the desktop.\r\nI can probably do a link to add to favourites but not to the desktop.\r\n\r\nPage 19 p5.5 should it be CLiC or CLIC as both are used in this paragraph.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nLooking at this new specification I have decided to use Rails as the Authlogic gem has the remember me and locked after failed attempts functionality built in.\r\nI will store users, practices and doctors in the database. Patient referrals will not be stored.\r\n\r\nYou may want to rethink all the admin happening behind the scenes if the data changes regularly.\r\n\r\nI have found a gem that should allow emails to be sent encrypted using PGP (GPG), though I will need to install and test to be sure and to figure out what keys are needed. \r\nOutlook will require a plugin to decrypt the emails. I have found http://www.gpg4win.org which provides a plugin for several version of outlook.\r\n\"Gpg4win runs on Windows XP, Vista, 7 and 8. Both 32 and 64bit systems are supported. \r\nThe Outlook plugin GpgOL is compatible with Microsoft Outlook 2003, 2007, 2010 and 2013 (only 32bit!). GpgOL supports MS Exchange Server in Outlook 2010 and 2013 only.\"\r\n\r\nWill a live and edge version be required?\r\n\r\nShould any links appear in the black menu bar?\r\n','2014-10-09 19:48:18'