INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES (1,1,NULL,'Agri energy','Process cooking oil into Biodiesel.\r\nFlash Gui to be developed by third party.\r\nWebsite/backend to be developed by Terrabase and to provide RESTful interface to Flash.',6,1,2,'2010-11-30 16:19:07','2010-11-30 16:22:20',0,0),(2,1,1,'RE: Agri energy','Requirements specification states to be written in ASP.NET with MS ACCESS 2010 database and to be run on AE server.\r\nRESTful interface was suggested thinking that it would be ROR on Terracloud.\r\nAlso need to interface with weighbridge and tank sensors.',6,0,NULL,'2010-11-30 16:22:20','2010-11-30 16:22:20',0,0),(3,1,NULL,'ESW Proposal','Drupal.org\r\n\r\nhttp://groups.drupal.org/node/19885#UK list of government sites using drupal\r\n\r\nTwitter plugin http://drupal.org/project/twitter\r\n\r\nFacebook plugin http://drupal.org/project/fbconnect\r\n\r\nEmbedded media http://drupal.org/project/emfield (not recently maintained)\r\n\r\nGallery http://drupal.org/project/image http://drupal.org/project/imagebrowser http://drupal.org/project/gallery_assist http://drupal.org/project/node_gallery http://drupal.org/project/node_gallery_jcarousel\r\n\r\nShopping Cart http://drupal.org/project/commerce or http://drupal.org/project/ubercart\r\n\r\nDocument system http://drupal.org/project/webfm http://drupal.org/project/filedepot\r\n\r\nSpell checking http://drupal.org/project/spellcheck http://drupal.org/project/wysiwyg_spellcheck (TinyMCE only)\r\n\r\nSite map http://drupal.org/project/site_map\r\n\r\n',6,1,4,'2011-02-15 17:06:18','2011-02-28 19:25:52',0,0),(4,1,3,'RE: ESW Proposal','Selected for interview but did not get contract.',6,0,NULL,'2011-02-28 19:25:52','2011-02-28 19:25:52',0,0),(9,3,NULL,'Update Meeting 15/01/2015','Attendees: David Craggs (DC), Tony Harris (TH)\r\nLocation: OfficeCraft\r\n\r\n1. Collaboration tools\r\n  - Use of forums on Redine\r\n  - Redmine login for DC\r\n  - Investigation of Office365 for document collaboration\r\n  - Set-up dropbox share between DC and TH\r\n  - Considered using Git for document management, but will probably stick to existing system for now\r\n\r\n2. Creation of an integrated company manual\r\n  - Existing documents and ISO manual will be brought to next meeting\r\n\r\n3. Set-up of Terrabase LinkedIn page\r\n\r\n4. Development of Graduate School proposal\r\n  - Draft to be completed by TH and sent to DC for review and strategic consideration\r\n\r\nNext meeting: Considered Friday 23rd January\r\n ',3,1,10,'2015-01-19 12:04:53','2015-01-20 10:53:03',0,0),(10,3,9,'RE: Update Meeting 15/01/2015','Had a look at Office365 - will start a new topic.\r\n\r\nFriday is still OK with me.',24,0,NULL,'2015-01-20 10:53:03','2015-01-20 10:53:03',0,0),(11,3,NULL,'Office365','I have set up an Office365 SharePoint site - I have sent an email out to Tony to connect. Is there anyone else who needs to connect?\r\n\r\nYou can add the site to Office so you can work on documents using the windows apps.\r\n\r\nIf this works out, we can do a site for Terrabase. \r\n\r\nThere is also the documents area in Redmine - has anyone used that? Although it looks more like a notepad looking at it.\r\n\r\nDave',24,7,26,'2015-01-20 10:58:42','2015-01-22 14:01:55',0,0),(12,3,11,'RE: Office365','I have tried editing a test document in both Word online and Word on my local machine. Seems to work ok. Do you see the changes ok Dave? Does it track changes, or do we need to turn that on?',3,0,NULL,'2015-01-20 15:38:14','2015-01-20 15:38:14',0,0),(13,3,NULL,'Scrum versus Agile','Has anyone any thoughts on Scrum/Agile processes?\r\n\r\nThere are Redmine plugins for both of these:\r\n\r\nhttp://www.redmine.org/plugins/redmine_agile\r\nhttp://www.redmine.org/plugins/scrum-plugin\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',24,12,33,'2015-01-20 15:57:56','2015-01-23 10:35:07',0,0),(14,3,11,'RE: Office365','Yes - I can see the changes. Not sure about tracking - probably need to switch it on.\r\n\r\nWill look tomorrow.',24,0,NULL,'2015-01-20 20:00:27','2015-01-20 20:00:27',0,0),(15,3,11,'RE: Office365','Right - had a look at Sharepoint and have enabled versioning and checking in and out. \r\n\r\nDo you want to have a go Tony?',24,0,NULL,'2015-01-21 14:27:24','2015-01-21 14:27:24',0,0),(16,3,11,'RE: Office365','Thanks Dave, I\'ll have a look.',3,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 07:59:53','2015-01-22 07:59:53',0,0),(17,3,13,'RE: Scrum versus Agile','They look useful, will do some further investigation.\r\n\r\nIt seems these forum don\'t notify me when there\'s an update. I have them set to Watch. I wonder if there\'s something we need to turn on. I\'ll check with Tracey.',3,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 08:01:34','2015-01-22 08:01:34',0,0),(18,3,13,'RE: Scrum versus Agile','Ok. Email notifications should be turned on now',3,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 08:03:23','2015-01-22 08:03:23',0,0),(19,3,13,'RE: Scrum versus Agile','Yes - just got the email notification.',24,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 09:26:43','2015-01-22 09:26:43',0,0),(20,3,13,'RE: Scrum versus Agile','Hmm - just got an email notification about my post - that\'s a bit clunky as I know I have posted. ',24,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 09:28:36','2015-01-22 09:28:36',0,0),(21,3,13,'RE: Scrum versus Agile','Ahh - found the setting to switch that off.',24,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 09:31:39','2015-01-22 09:31:39',0,0),(22,3,13,'RE: Scrum versus Agile','Some thoughts on implementing Scrum with Redmine:\r\n\r\n* Product Owner creates a project in Redmine. Uploads specification and creates the milestones (issues with unassigned priorities). Put a deadlines for the milestones and estimated staff hours.\r\n\r\n* The ScrumMaster checks the milestones in and arranges the Sprint planning meeting\r\n	Part 1: Dev Team, Scrum Master, Product Owner\r\n	Part 2: Dev Team\r\n\r\n* Produces: Sprint Backlog that gets broken down as issues on Redmine with priorities and timings.\r\n\r\n* ScrumMaster arranges, chairs and documents daily scrum\r\n\r\n* Multiple projects should be handled as separate scrum meetings held one after the next\r\n\r\n* Urgent issues are added to a project with a deadline and CRVT priority and handled by the ScrumMaster',3,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 11:32:49','2015-01-22 11:32:49',0,0),(23,3,11,'RE: Office365','Seems to work well.\r\n\r\nJust a couple a queries:\r\n\r\nI\'ve tried to set it so I can follow a document which I assume means I get notified if there are any changes, but I don\'t seem to be able to get it working. It says I\'m not set-up to do that.\r\n\r\nAnd I was wondering, if I have a document checked-out does that mean others cannot also check it out until I check it back in again? I assume that is the case.',3,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 11:56:00','2015-01-22 11:56:00',0,0),(24,3,11,'RE: Office365','The require check out is an option \r\n\r\n\"Details here\":https://support.office.com/client/results.aspx?Shownav=true&lcid=1033&ns=SPOSTANDARD&version=16&helpID=RequireCheckout&ver=16&services=YAMMER_ENTERPRISE%2cRMS_S_ENTERPRISE%2cOFFICESUBSCRIPTION%2cMCOSTANDARD%2cSHAREPOINTWAC%2cSHAREPOINTENTERPRISE%2cEXCHANGE_S_ENTERPRISE&ui=en-US&rs=en-GB&ad=GB\r\n\r\nHmm - not sure about the follow option. Seems to work for me.\r\n',24,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 12:39:22','2015-01-22 12:39:22',0,0),(25,3,13,'RE: Scrum versus Agile','Looks like a good start. Have you installed the Redmine Scrum plugin?\r\n\r\nDo we need a separate project for this? \r\n',24,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 13:10:39','2015-01-22 13:10:39',0,0),(26,3,11,'RE: Office365','Notification seems to be working now.',3,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 14:01:55','2015-01-22 14:01:55',0,0),(27,3,NULL,'Scrum','Some Links\r\n\r\n\"Training Videos\":http://scrumtrainingseries.com\r\n\r\n\"Scrum Reference Card\":http://www.collab.net/sites/default/files/uploads/CollabNet_scrumreferencecard.pdf\r\n\r\n\"ScrumMaster CheckList\":http://www.scrummasterchecklist.org/\r\n',24,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 14:22:23','2015-01-22 14:22:23',0,0),(28,3,13,'RE: Scrum versus Agile','Both the Redmine plugins require at least version 2.3.x. The Terrabase Redmine is currently version 1.4.4 so Redmine would require upgrading before either plugin could be installed.',6,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 20:30:56','2015-01-22 20:30:56',0,0),(29,3,13,'RE: Scrum versus Agile','That\'s two and a half years old. Looks like a lot has changed between versions. Is it a big job to upgrade do you know?',24,0,NULL,'2015-01-22 22:14:38','2015-01-22 22:14:38',0,0),(30,3,NULL,'Redmine Issue Protocol with specifications','The plan is to include the updates to proof-reading issues as part of a system specification. So a specification is written, and an issue is created to proof-read that spec. If the spec is to go out to a client then the spec is updated and re-released for proofing until it is all correct. Once it is correct it is released to the customer as version 1.0.0\r\n\r\nAn issue is then created to build the system according to the spec (Scrum procedure may modify this). Any further changes to the spec should be noted in the issue and the issue becomes part of the spec unless another release is required to the customer, at which point the items in the issue are all rolled up into version 2.0.0\r\n\r\nSmall changes to the spec, such as spelling or literary errors increase the revision by 1, and structural changes which affect programming increase the minor version.\r\n\r\nI have not followed this procedure with #1460 and #1454. To correct this I have updated #1454 with the notes from the proof read and updated the released specification to v1.0.0 so it now complies more with the procedure.\r\n\r\nAny thoughts?',3,0,NULL,'2015-01-23 08:33:33','2015-01-23 08:33:33',0,0),(31,3,13,'RE: Scrum versus Agile','I have been playing with setting up a test Redmine installation on windows - but it is proving hard work.\r\n\r\nThis morning I downloaded a \"Bitnami Ubuntu Redmine VMWare\":https://bitnami.com/stack/redmine image and am now up and running. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',24,0,NULL,'2015-01-23 10:17:25','2015-01-23 10:17:25',0,0),(32,3,13,'RE: Scrum versus Agile','Hmm - is there an Ubuntu for Dummies book? :-)\r\n',24,0,NULL,'2015-01-23 10:21:33','2015-01-23 10:21:33',0,0),(33,3,13,'RE: Scrum versus Agile','There is no GUI installed. As a newbie - should I install one? If so, any recommendations?',24,0,NULL,'2015-01-23 10:35:07','2015-01-23 10:35:07',0,0),(34,3,NULL,'Ruby','Which version of Ruby are we using?\r\n\r\nNeed to make sure I am using the right stack.',24,2,36,'2015-02-06 15:28:33','2015-02-06 16:07:32',0,0),(35,3,34,'RE: Ruby','All but  3 legacy applications run Ruby MRI 1.9.3-p194.',6,0,NULL,'2015-02-06 15:44:56','2015-02-06 15:44:56',0,0),(36,3,34,'RE: Ruby','Ah - got 2.1.5 here. \r\n\r\nWill download 1.9.3 and give that a go.',24,0,NULL,'2015-02-06 16:07:32','2015-02-06 16:07:32',0,0),(37,4,NULL,'Logic for automatic action creation','Just wondering if you could confirm how the logic for the automatic DBS action creation feature works so I can give CWaC a definitive answer',3,1,42,'2015-02-09 10:43:22','2015-02-11 18:15:33',0,0),(38,5,NULL,'Including primary and secondary categories to graphs','How easy would it be to include primary and secondary project code categories in the graphs dropdown in the dashboard.\r\n\r\nSelecting primary as the category and relative enrolments as the data would show all enrolments on courses belonging to project codes across the categories. Likewise for the secondary category',3,1,43,'2015-02-09 11:00:19','2015-02-11 19:11:22',0,0),(39,6,NULL,'Groups for providers','What would be involved in having a groups look-up and allow users to select zero or more groups for a provider to belong to (i.e. a checkbox list control in provider screen listing all the groups).\r\n\r\nAlso - When an action is copied allow a group to be selected and copy the action to all the providers in the group',3,1,44,'2015-02-09 11:06:00','2015-02-11 19:22:49',0,0),(40,7,NULL,'Email receive plug-in','It would be good to set-up the email receive plug-in so that emails can be forwarded to Redmine and automatically added into projects. Perhaps with some kind of parsing so we can have a bit of control over how Redmine handles it',3,1,41,'2015-02-09 11:20:40','2015-02-09 11:31:04',0,0),(41,7,40,'RE: Email receive plug-in','From this page\r\n\r\nhttp://www.redmine.org/projects/redmine/wiki/RedmineReceivingEmails\r\n\r\nThere is this:\r\n\r\n> _Setup\r\n> \r\n> You can configure Redmine to receive emails in one of the following ways:\r\n> •Forwarding emails from your email server: ?Pros: works with a remote mail server, email are processed instantly, fast (no environment reloading)\r\n> ?Cons: needs some configuration on your mail transfer agent (eg. Postfix, Sendmail...)\r\n> \r\n> •Fetching emails from an IMAP or POP3 server: ?Pros: easy to setup, no need to configure your MTA, works with a remote mail server\r\n> ?Cons: emails are not processed instantly (a cron job needs to be added to read emails periodically)\r\n> \r\n> •Reading emails from standard input: ?Pros: fine for testing purpose\r\n> ?Cons: slow (the environment is reloaded each time an email is read), needs some configuration on your MTA\r\n> _\r\n> \r\n\r\nIs it possible to set up a terrabase pop3 account for Redmine?\r\n\r\n',24,0,NULL,'2015-02-09 11:31:04','2015-02-09 11:31:04',0,0),(42,4,37,'RE: Logic for automatic action creation','If the renewal date is blank or before 1 month from now then an action will be created unless an action already exists and is not completed.\r\n\r\nThis check will be made every night, if the renewal date or providers are changed when updating a tutor and when adding a new tutor.',6,0,NULL,'2015-02-11 18:15:33','2015-02-11 18:15:33',0,0),(43,5,38,'RE: Including primary and secondary categories to graphs','Shouldn\'t take more than half a day.\r\nWe already do charts for project providers and fundings so the logic should be similar. \r\nI assume you would want all chart types.',6,0,NULL,'2015-02-11 19:11:22','2015-02-11 19:11:22',0,0),(44,6,39,'RE: Groups for providers','We would need Groups adding to look-up management to allow the Groups to be created/edited and deleted.\r\n\r\nNot sure what you mean by a check-box list control? \r\nDo you mean a check-box for each group? This could become unmanageable if there are a lot of groups.\r\nDo you mean a multi-select list where there is a scrollable list of options which the user can ctrl click to select multiple options? \r\nOr did you mean something else?\r\n\r\nWould there be 2 drop-down/links? The copy to provider which is the current functionality and copy to group (drop-down would be all groups) which would be the new functionality.\r\nI assume this would iterate through all providers in the selected group (excluding the current provider) and create an action in the same way as currently.  ',6,0,NULL,'2015-02-11 19:22:49','2015-02-11 19:22:49',0,0),(45,3,NULL,'Ruby on Rails','I\'m giving up on windows, too many gotchas with gems that don\'t really work with Windows. Now trying Ubuntu, will need help!!!',24,1,47,'2015-02-12 13:25:41','2015-02-17 12:14:34',0,0),(46,8,NULL,'ESAR Project Definition','pdf in Dropbox/Share/IPMS/ESAR\r\n\r\nTracey\r\n\r\n\"I assume this is a new application which uses the Portal for Single Sign on.\r\n\r\nI assume that the design will be similar to the other IPMS applications, probably closest to RPM as that has a similar endless list.\r\n\r\nWhat style do you want for the buttons?\r\n\r\nWhat roles are available in the application ? Is it just Admin? If not what permissions do the other roles have.\r\n\r\nI assume the ESAR Master Screen is not in a modal dialogue but on the actual page.\r\n\r\nOnce an ESAR is created what happens if the Analysis changes status to Draft or more likely Archived? Should the ESAR still be available and updateable?\r\n\r\nWhat happens if the Analysis id deleted after the ESAR is created. It will be impossible to calculate the figures for changes to quick-filter, or depending on design to changes to the aspect?\r\n\r\nWhat field does the Time period refer to? I assume if the field is null the record should be excluded. Should the From and To fields have the standard date picker?\r\n\r\nWhat options are available in the category drop-down? Is it the same as Aldas and if so should it be kep in sync with Aldas if it changes in the future?\r\n\r\nWhat is the difference between the Termly Dataset and the Full Year Dataset, in Fig 3.1 they look identical\r\n\r\nI assume the fields in Fig3.2 are just free text fields or text areas with no validation.\r\n\r\nP3.6 can we considered that at a later date, not sure how to allow a user to draw freehand.\r\n\r\nFig 3.3 Full range of ESAR Elements\r\n\r\nNot sure how to calculate most of these. Could you provide the formulas/calculations before I implement ESAR.\r\nDo the 5 columns have any significance, i.e should the items just be listed in the drop-down, or should they be grouped by column?\r\n\r\nWhat does the PDF look like?\r\n\r\nWhat does the exported xls look like? The library I use for creating spreadsheets can\'t cope with graphs or images.\r\n\r\nNote:\r\n\r\nThe graphs will not appear instantly is going to take a while to calculate the data and generate the graphs, not sure how long until I get it working. I plan to put a generating message while its generating.\r\n\r\nAldas will need changes to provide the API\'s to get the data. It may actually work out easier to do the calculations in Aldas and just return the results to ESAR.\"',3,0,NULL,'2015-02-12 14:25:34','2015-02-12 14:26:01',0,0),(47,3,45,'RE: Ruby on Rails','Now got a working system.\r\n\r\nWorking through a ruby on rails demo...\r\n\r\nWatch this space!',24,0,NULL,'2015-02-17 12:14:34','2015-02-17 12:14:34',0,0),(49,25,NULL,'Forum usage protocol','Here are some suggestions for how we should use forums. Please add comments/other ideas\r\n\r\n* When sending an email always consider whether using a forum would be a better option then we have a record against projects that everyone can see\r\n* Email should only be used if the message needs to be private\r\n* Forums should not be used to manage issues. Identify issues from forum messages and create the issue accordingly.\r\n* All forums you have access to should be watched so there is email notification\r\n* The \'Terrabase\' project forums are for everyone so everyone should have access to the Terrabase forum\r\n* If a message relates to many projects is might be worth putting it in the Terrabase project forums, or if it is to do with infrastructure development projects then consider the Terrabase Infrastructure forums\r\n* Project specific forums should only contain messages mainly relating to that project.\r\n* Customer/staff/pricing/confidential client information should be kept out of these forums\r\n* Treat forum items as \'priority 2\' (i.e. respond to a forum item as soon as convenient)',3,6,58,'2015-02-18 15:20:50','2015-02-18 17:56:05',0,0),(50,25,49,'RE: Forum usage protocol','Surely this is project related not everyone will necessarily have access to all projects.\r\n\r\n> •Terrabase forums are for everyone so everyone should have access to the Terrabase forum\r\n\r\nWhat about forums that may have customer access?',24,0,NULL,'2015-02-18 15:32:01','2015-02-18 15:32:01',0,0),(51,25,49,'RE: Forum usage protocol','I was thinking of giving everyone access to the Terrabase project, which I think is possible without giving access to all projects.\r\n\r\nI\'m not sure about forums with customer access unless we create projects specifically for customer access, but I think that might get messy.',3,0,NULL,'2015-02-18 17:28:06','2015-02-18 17:29:15',0,0),(52,25,NULL,'Ruby Devepment Document','Discussion around this draft Ruby Development Document.',3,0,NULL,'2015-02-18 17:31:38','2015-02-18 17:31:38',0,0),(53,25,49,'RE: Forum usage protocol','I have added another item\r\n\r\n\"Treat forum items as \'priority 2\' (i.e. respond to a forum item as soon as convenient)\"',3,0,NULL,'2015-02-18 17:36:01','2015-02-18 17:36:01',0,0),(54