t compatible with other ruby managers,\r\nyou can switch to \'.ruby-version\' using \'rvm rvmrc to ruby-version\'\r\nor ignore this warning with \'rvm rvmrc warning ignore /home/dcraggs/RubymineProjects/TerraBase/gpsecure/.rvmrc\',\r\n\'.rvmrc\' will continue to be the default project file in RVM 1 and RVM 2,\r\nto ignore the warning for all files run \'rvm rvmrc warning ignore all.rvmrcs\'.\r\n\r\nIs this a bad thing????',24,1,73,'2015-02-19 17:33:51','2015-02-19 17:35:37',0,0),(73,25,72,'RE: .rvmrc','No its not, just say yes to trust it. You wont see it again for this project.',6,0,NULL,'2015-02-19 17:35:37','2015-02-19 17:35:37',0,0),(74,25,69,'RE: GPSecure and ARTDT','Still getting the problem.\r\n\r\nCreate the gemsert\r\nran - rvm use 1.9.3-p194@gpsecure\r\nran - bundle install\r\nran - gem update\r\n\r\ndcraggs@kRubyDev:~/RubymineProjects/TerraBase/gpsecure$ gem update\r\nUpdating installed gems\r\nUpdating slop\r\nERROR:  Error installing slop:\r\n        slop requires Ruby version >= 2.0.0.\r\nGems updated: slop\r\n\r\n\r\nMay need a visit from you at some stage to put me right!!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',24,0,NULL,'2015-02-19 17:39:29','2015-02-19 17:39:29',0,0),(75,25,69,'RE: GPSecure and ARTDT','Why did you gem update? That attempts to update all the gems to their latest versions, you already had the gems versions you needed after the bundle install.',6,0,NULL,'2015-02-19 17:41:23','2015-02-19 17:41:23',0,0),(76,25,69,'RE: GPSecure and ARTDT','Because I don\'t really know what I am doing :-)',24,0,NULL,'2015-02-19 18:03:14','2015-02-19 18:03:14',0,0),(77,25,69,'RE: GPSecure and ARTDT','@bundle clean --force@ will remove all gems/versions in the gemset that are not in the Gemfile.lock. \r\n\r\nDo not run this if you are not using a gemset as it will remove all gems not in the current Gemfile.lock which could remove gems required by other projects.',6,0,NULL,'2015-02-19 18:17:08','2015-02-19 18:17:08',0,0),(78,25,NULL,'Forums','I think we need to rationalise the forums for each project I\'m not sure we need as much granularity. I am already finding it hard to locate messages I want to comae back to.\r\n\r\nI think we would be better with just one forum per project - and also name is properly, so it \"Project Name\" General Discussion. Having them all called the same can confuse - well it can confuse me, but then I\'m easily confused :-)\r\n\r\n',24,3,117,'2015-02-21 12:56:41','2015-03-10 19:12:14',0,0),(79,87,NULL,'WARN Messages','On running artdt I am getting a lo of these messages:\r\n\r\nWARN  Could not determine content-length of response body. Set content-length of the response or set Response#chunked = true\r\n\r\nApparently this is a problem with Webrick and one solution seems to be to use Thin instead.\r\n\r\nhttp://rorguide.blogspot.co.uk/2014/02/solution-to-remove-warning-could-not.html\r\n\r\nAny thoughts on this Tracy?',24,2,90,'2015-02-21 13:05:50','2015-02-26 10:20:21',0,0),(80,87,NULL,'Tab order','There seems to be an issue with the tab order on the assessments dialog.\r\n\r\nIf you click in contact name and then start tabbing you don\'t get the next field. \r\n\r\nLooking at it clicking in (or out) of the edit fields causes a hit on the database and a page refresh. This seems to be an update to the users table setting the last_request_at and updated_at fields.\r\n\r\nI did discuss this with Tony and it seems top be happening on the live system as well.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',24,9,99,'2015-02-21 13:23:23','2015-02-26 18:02:28',0,0),(81,87,NULL,'Form size','Just wondering why the assessments view is a fixed dialog rather than full screen? Means lot\'s of scrolling on a bigger screen.',24,1,84,'2015-02-21 15:58:54','2015-02-23 10:00:59',0,0),(82,87,NULL,'Sorting','When Tony and I looked at artdt last week we noted that the client selection dropdown box was not sorted.\r\n\r\nLooking at the code, Changing:\r\n\r\n<%= text_field_tag :client_name, \'\', class: \'autocomplete\', data: {clients: Client.active.map {|c| {value: c.name, id: c.id }}.to_json }%>\r\n\r\nto \r\n\r\n<%= text_field_tag :client_name, \'\', class: \'autocomplete\', data: {clients: Client.active.sort_by { |c| c.name}.map {|c| {value: c.name, id: c.id }}.to_json }%>\r\n\r\nin assessments/new.html.erb does the job. Is that the best way?',24,3,92,'2015-02-22 13:53:55','2015-02-26 10:26:20',0,0),(83,87,80,'RE: Tab order','I seem to remember the elements need to check with the database when changes are made as this determines whether the other tabs are enabled or not. Something along those lines.\r\n\r\nThere shouldn\'t actually be any page refreshes, it should be all done with js.',3,0,NULL,'2015-02-23 09:59:59','2015-02-23 09:59:59',0,0),(84,87,81,'RE: Form size','Only because the client wasn\'t in a position to pay for a responsive design.',3,0,NULL,'2015-02-23 10:00:59','2015-02-23 10:00:59',0,0),(85,87,80,'RE: Tab order','If you edit a client, click into the contact name then click into telephone number this happens:\r\n\r\n\r\n Started PUT \"/assessments/37\" for 127.0.0.1 at 2015-02-22 02:51:29 +0000\r\nProcessing by AssessmentsController#update as JS\r\n  Parameters: {\"utf8\"=>\"?\", \"authenticity_token\"=>\"JIkuCD8CJyB+yv5PSDrpZ5TDBI6SfkZqLkpEw0Qmujs=\", \"assessment\"=>{\"client_attributes\"=>{\"organisation_type\"=>\"organisation\", \"name\"=>\"\", \"main_contact_name\"=>\"\", \"contact_phone\"=>\"\", \"contact_email\"=>\"\", \"organisation_website\"=>\"\", \"postal_address\"=>\"\", \"postcode\"=>\"\", \"legal_structure\"=>\"\", \"other_legal_structure\"=>\"\", \"activities\"=>\"\", \"other_activity\"=>\"\", \"services_to\"=>\"\", \"other_service\"=>\"\", \"total_income\"=>\"\", \"no_of_paid_staff\"=>\"\", \"no_of_trustees\"=>\"\", \"no_of_volunteers\"=>\"\", \"id\"=>\"6\"}, \"contact_name\"=>\"\", \"telephone_number\"=>\"\", \"contact_email\"=>\"\", \"role_within_organisation\"=>\"\", \"accept_confirmation\"=>\"false\"}, \"id\"=>\"37\"}\r\n  User Load (0.1ms)  SELECT `users`.* FROM `users` WHERE `users`.`id` = 1 LIMIT 1\r\n   (0.1ms)  BEGIN\r\n   (1.7ms)  UPDATE `users` SET `last_request_at` = \'2015-02-22 02:51:29\', `updated_at` = \'2015-02-22 02:51:29\' WHERE `users`.`id` = 1\r\n   (1.0ms)  COMMIT\r\n  Assessment Load (0.1ms)  SELECT `assessments`.* FROM `assessments` WHERE `assessments`.`id` = 37 LIMIT 1\r\n  Client Load (0.1ms)  SELECT `clients`.* FROM `clients` WHERE `clients`.`id` = 6 LIMIT 1\r\n   (0.0ms)  BEGIN\r\n  Client Exists (0.2ms)  SELECT 1 AS one FROM `clients` WHERE (`clients`.`name` = BINARY \'\' AND `clients`.`id` != 6) LIMIT 1\r\n   (0.1ms)  ROLLBACK\r\n  Rendered assessments/_general_details.html.erb (9.7ms)\r\n  Rendered assessments/update.js.erb (11.4ms)\r\nCompleted 200 OK in 30.7ms (Views: 13.5ms | ActiveRecord: 3.3ms)\r\n\r\n\r\nI\'m trying to get my head around what is going on the background.',24,0,NULL,'2015-02-23 10:15:09','2015-02-23 10:15:09',0,0),(86,87,80,'RE: Tab order','The form data is being posted to the server whenever a drop-down is changed, a text field or textarea is left, or a radio-button is changed.\r\n\r\nThe specification required the form to automatically be submitted without the user needing to press a save button.\r\n\r\nIn the above log the validation fails hence the Rollback and the form is re-shown with the validation error highlighted in red, the client name can\'t be blank.\r\n\r\nThe form being replaced with a new copy with the latest errors/warnings means that the tab position is lost and starts from the first field again. I added code to ensure that the scroll position was remembered.\r\n\r\nThe code is in app/assets/javascripts/assessments.js.coffee. Particularly the @formLoaded@ function and the @submitForm@ function.\r\n\r\nI hadn\'t realized that this functionality broke tabbing thorough fields.\r\n',6,0,NULL,'2015-02-25 19:47:52','2015-02-25 19:47:52',0,0),(87,87,82,'RE: Sorting','<%= text_field_tag :client_name, \'\', class: \'autocomplete\', data: {clients: Client.active.order(:name).map {|c| {value: c.name, id: c.id }}.to_json }%>\r\n\r\nIs better as the sort is done by the database not to the array once the records are retrieved.',6,0,NULL,'2015-02-25 19:51:18','2015-02-25 19:51:18',0,0),(88,87,79,'RE: WARN Messages','Webrick is a very basic webserver.\r\n\r\nI don\'t use Webrick for testing as I run all the websites using Apache with Passenger so I have never had this problem. \r\nI prefer to use an environment as close to the live server as possible.',6,0,NULL,'2015-02-25 19:55:43','2015-02-25 19:55:43',0,0),(89,87,82,'RE: Sorting','Thanks Tracey guess there\'s not much in it though.\r\n\r\nTony - has should be put in as an issue.',24,0,NULL,'2015-02-26 10:15:02','2015-02-26 10:15:02',0,0),(90,87,79,'RE: WARN Messages','Will have to see about setting that up then.',24,0,NULL,'2015-02-26 10:20:21','2015-02-26 10:20:21',0,0),(91,87,80,'RE: Tab order','It\'s worse than that, the check box fields get cleared.\r\n\r\nQuestion is how to get round this.\r\n\r\nAlso highlights the need for some proper testing. Tony and I have discussed this, we both agree that developers are NOT the best people to test their own code. I know I don\'t do a thorough job of testing my code, and my time is better spent elsewhere. I have someone we may be able to bring on board, I use him for testing a lot of my stuff from NATS, he is very picky, but that is what you want from a tester.',24,0,NULL,'2015-02-26 10:26:11','2015-02-26 10:26:11',0,0),(92,87,82,'RE: Sorting','Covered in issue 1496. Are you able to create a sub-task related to it?',3,0,NULL,'2015-02-26 10:26:20','2015-02-26 10:26:20',0,0),(93,87,80,'RE: Tab order','I am a terrible tester, as Tracey will testify!\r\n\r\nA good tester would be great if we can get a client to cover the costs.',3,0,NULL,'2015-02-26 10:31:46','2015-02-26 10:31:46',0,0),(94,77,NULL,'GP Secure issues','\r\n\r\nWhat can the admin user do? Can\'t seen any admin options or am, I missing something?\r\n\r\nWill have a look at exim4 when I have a moment.\r\n\r\n============================================================================================\r\nItems below from email\r\n============================================================================================\r\n\r\nFrom Tracey:\r\n_\r\n\r\nThe admin should not have a practice_id as they should never enter referral details. There is an issue 1486 which would prevent admin users seeing the referral form.\r\n\r\nThere is very little validation except on field lengths as all the fields are optional except the doctor and the first doctor is pre-selected.\r\n\r\nI use exim4 on both the live server and on my development PC so it just uses the default sendmail configuration.\r\nI have exim4 configured to only send and receive emails locally on my development PC to prevent any accidental emails to other people being sent.\r\n\r\nYour suggested configuration looks reasonable and would normally be put into an initializer. e.g. config/initializers/action_mailer.rb.\r\nIf you don\'t check this file into git, it allows each developer to use there own configuration and stops your username and password being visible to everyone with access to the git repository. It also prevents the configuration appearing on the live server.\r\n_\r\nOn 22/02/15 16:32, David Craggs wrote:\r\nGot GPSecure working.\r\n\r\nHad to update the admin user to add the practice field as initially the dropdown list was blank  - still allowed me to send though. Doesn\'t seem to be any validation yet.\r\n\r\nHow should the smtp server setting be configured? Is it done at system level or application?\r\n\r\nThis seems to be the code, but where to put it? In the environments rb files?\r\n\r\nconfig.action_mailer.delivery_method = :smtp\r\nconfig.action_mailer.smtp_settings = {\r\n  address:              \'smtp.gmail.com\',\r\n  port:                 587,\r\n  domain:               \'example.com\',\r\n  user_name:            \'<username>\',\r\n  password:             \'<password>\',\r\n  authentication:       \'plain\',\r\n  enable_starttls_auto: true  }\r\n\r\nDave\r\n',24,1,98,'2015-02-26 10:47:00','2015-02-26 17:12:19',0,0),(95,87,80,'RE: Tab order','In the future it may be worth trying to include testing in the quotes.\r\n\r\nIf you let too many bugs and niggles get through it can seriously affect credibility IMHO.\r\n\r\nAlso do you have version numbers anywhere on your websites? When testing it is useful to know what version you are testing against and what has changed for that version.',24,0,NULL,'2015-02-26 10:58:15','2015-02-26 10:58:15',0,0),(96,87,80,'RE: Tab order','Yes indeed. We tend to have to go through a significant amount of client \'self-testing\' due to budget limitations.\r\n\r\nVersion numbers need revisiting. They haven\'t been of significant value with our existing methodology but I can see the need for this to change.\r\n\r\nI was considering relating version numbers of all developments to include the sprint where that version was released (eg. 2015.5.1) which could help when referring back to notes and discussions.',3,0,NULL,'2015-02-26 11:15:06','2015-02-26 11:15:06',0,0),(97,87,80,'RE: Tab order','You have to be careful not to give users products top test that are too \'buggy\' - can really give the wrong impression!!',24,0,NULL,'2015-02-26 11:59:10','2015-02-26 11:59:10',0,0),(98,77,94,'RE: GP Secure issues','An admin can click the link in the referral email and then see the decrypted referral details, they can also login and logout.\r\n\r\nThe users, practices and doctors are maintained by importing a spreadsheet so no web interface for maintaining them.',6,0,NULL,'2015-02-26 17:12:19','2015-02-26 17:12:19',0,0),(99,87,80,'RE: Tab order','The check boxes in the general tab don\'t do anything, they are there as the specification showed them, but it never stated what their function was. The check box values are not stored in the database so will never be remembered.\r\n\r\nThe check boxes on the other tabs do function correctly and are remembered.\r\n\r\n',6,0,NULL,'2015-02-26 18:02:28','2015-02-26 18:02:28',0,0),(100,93,NULL,'Booking system for Imperial Academic English','Imperial are after a booking system where a logged-in student can see available appointment slots for their tutor and can request the appointment. I guess the appointment would then be pending until confirmed or otherwise by the lecturer. The lecturer needs to be able to save the booking into Outlook.\r\n\r\nJust wondering if there\'s a system out there (RoR/open-source) that would do the trick or at least be a starting point for us.',3,4,104,'2015-03-03 13:49:14','2015-03-03 17:24:43',0,0),(101,93,100,'RE: Booking system for Imperial Academic English','I\'ve had a look at a couple of things. This gets the closest\r\n\r\nhttp://www.supersaas.co.uk/schedule/Terrabase/Lecturers\r\n\r\nBut I would want it to automatically select the correct lecturer for the student (i.e. it would need a back-end to link lecturers to students) and I would lecturers to be able to manage their own appointment times individually',3,0,NULL,'2015-03-03 13:56:09','2015-03-03 13:56:09',0,0),(102,93,100,'RE: Booking system for Imperial Academic English','Is this a whole new system? How much integration is needed with outlook?\r\n\r\nAre the available slots going to be in outlook or somewhere else or both!\r\n\r\nHow are they using outlook? Is it part of an Exchange system? ',24,0,NULL,'2015-03-03 14:30:37','2015-03-03 14:30:37',0,0),(103,93,100,'RE: Booking system for Imperial Academic English','If this is for the Graduate school there are several Moodle plugins that may be of interest.\r\n\r\n\"Booking\":https://moodle.org/plugins/view/mod_booking\r\n\r\n\"FacetoFace\":https://moodle.org/plugins/view/mod_facetoface\r\n\r\n\"Scheduler\":https://moodle.org/plugins/view.php?plugin=mod_scheduler',6,0,NULL,'2015-03-03 15:50:09','2015-03-03 15:50:09',0,0),(104,93,100,'RE: Booking system for Imperial Academic English','Re: Dave - At this stage it is a whole new system and stand-alone. The only Outlook integration required is an event download (iCal or some-such). The available slots would probably be in the web interface. I don\'t think they are on exchange, we connect to the Imperial mail server as part of the Imperial Horizons system and I guess they use the same server.\r\n\r\nRe: Tracey - Those Moodle plug-ins look interesting, and it might be a way to get them into Moodle in general, there might be value we could add. I\'ll take a further look.\r\n\r\nThanks.',3,0,NULL,'2015-03-03 17:24:43','2015-03-03 17:24:43',0,0),(105,45,NULL,'Setting compulsory fields','Does anyone know if it is possible to set other fields, not just custom ones, to be Required? I am wanting to force myself to add an estimated time and due by date when I create an issue.',3,1,108,'2015-03-04 11:28:30','2015-03-04 16:23:49',0,0),(108,45,105,'RE: Setting compulsory fields','It should be possible in the latest version, so try with the new Redmine install.\r\n',6,0,NULL,'2015-03-04 16:23:49','2015-03-04 16:23:49',0,0),(110,44,NULL,'About: Question plugins in redmine','The question plugins has been added in test redmine, but when updating issue and open \'Assign question to:\' choice gives only Ayman Attaie (user) and Anyone, the other users not appear, any idea about this issue?',22,4,114,'2015-03-05 13:48:33','2015-03-10 11:23:40',0,0),(111,44,110,'RE: About: Question plugins in redmine','Are the other users associated with the project as it should only show users that can see the project.',6,0,NULL,'2015-03-05 15:46:34','2015-03-05 15:46:34',0,0),(112,44,110,'RE: About: Question plugins in redmine','Thank you Tracey all users appeared when I add the users to the issue. But other error generated when updating the issue and assign a question to user with Note (only), (without adding note will success).\r\nthe error message: \r\n((*Internal error\r\n\r\nAn error occurred on the page you were trying to access.\r\nIf you continue to experience problems please contact your Redmine administrator for assistance.\r\n\r\nIf you are the Redmine administrator, check your log files for details about the error. )) \r\nAny idea? ',22,0,NULL,'2015-03-09 15:11:01','2015-03-09 15:35:09',0,0),(113,44,110,'RE: About: Question plugins in redmine','What does the log show? (log/production.log)',6,0,NULL,'2015-03-09 17:24:41','2015-03-09 17:24:41',0,0),(114,44,110,'RE: About: Question plugins in redmine','This what has been recorded in production.log after submitting a question:\r\n\r\n{{Started PUT \"/issues/6\" for 192.168.5.102 at 2015-03-10 11:19:28 +0000\r\nProcessing by IssuesController#update as HTML\r\n  Parameters: {\"utf8\"=>\"?\", \"authenticity_token\"=>\"1N/aUHsX82YIz++qXVlGYUcPu2ukLr/8NLYTBkz3hCo=\", \"issue\"=>{\"is_private\"=>\"0\", \"tracker_id\"=>\"1\", \"subject\"=>\"Thi is a test issue\", \"description\"=>\"\", \"status_id\"=>\"1\", \"priority_id\"=>\"4\", \"assigned_to_id\"=>\"7\", \"parent_issue_id\"=>\"\", \"start_date\"=>\"2015-02-24\", \"due_date\"=>\"\", \"estimated_hours\"=>\"\", \"done_ratio\"=>\"0\", \"notes\"=>\"test2\", \"private_notes\"=>\"0\", \"lock_version\"=>\"1\"}, \"time_entry\"=>{\"hours\"=>\"\", \"activity_id\"=>\"\", \"comments\"=>\"\"}, \"note\"=>{\"question_assigned_to\"=>\"7\"}, \"last_journal_id\"=>\"\", \"commit\"=>\"Submit\", \"id\"=>\"6\"}\r\n  Current user: testredmine (id=4)\r\n  Rendered mailer/_issue.text.erb (6.2ms)\r\n  Rendered mailer/issue_edit.text.erb within layouts/mailer (7.4ms)\r\n  Rendered mailer/_issue.html.erb (1.0ms)\r\n  Rendered mailer/issue_edit.html.erb within layouts/mailer (2.4ms)\r\n  Rendered mailer/_issue.text.erb (17.0ms)\r\n  Rendered plugins/question_plugin/app/views/question_mailer/asked_question.erb within layouts/mailer (18.1ms)\r\nCompleted 500 Internal Server Error in 570.3ms\r\n\r\nActionView::Template::Error (undefined local variable or method `users\' for #<#<Class:0xa2591f8>:0xb56fdac8>):\r\n    1: <%= \"#{issue.tracker.name} ##{issue