INSERT INTO `news` VALUES (2,15,'New forum format','Each project now has a standard set of forums','All development projects have the following format:\r\n\r\n*General discussion* - General discussion area\r\n*Ideas* - Discussion of ideas\r\n*Features and functionality* - Anything to do with how features and functions work	\r\n*Future development* - Discussion around possible future development features and proposals\r\n\r\nApart from the Terrabase parent project which has the following format:\r\n\r\n*General discussion* - Anything general not specifically related to a project\r\n*New Projects and Proposals* - For discussing brand new projects and proposals before they have a space on Redmine	\r\n*Strategic Team Meetings* - Minutes, agendas and comments from Strategic Team Meetings',3,'2015-02-14 18:44:19',0),(4,50,'New overview page format','A new overview page format is in place','Initially in place on the ART Diagnostic Tool project. Have created a forum to discuss it. Please add your thoughts.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.terrabase.co.uk/redmine/boards/25/topics/55',3,'2015-02-18 17:46:17',0),(5,51,'Being reviewed for expansion by NHS managers','','This system is currently rolled out across the Wirral but is currently under review by NHS managers for roll-out across the North-west',3,'2015-02-19 12:24:14',0),(6,50,'Status update','','Awaiting release of version 1.0.0. This will mark the delivery of the fully usable system excepting management reports which will need to be developed over the coming months.',3,'2015-02-19 13:00:58',0),(7,43,'Status update','','This website was converted over a year ago to a Forward to the SaughallBlades Facebook page',3,'2015-02-19 13:23:11',0),(8,36,'Status update','','Hosting renewed for another year on 1st Jan 2015. No other issues to report.',3,'2015-02-19 13:41:52',0),(9,29,'Nothing to report!','','This website sits on a Squarespace account which the client pays for an manages. There has been no activity on this project since October 2012',3,'2015-02-20 14:22:07',0),(10,48,'New overview page format in place','','I have put the new overview page in place for IHMS. Included is a link to the General Internal Project Share which contains a spec of some recent developments including the Generic Report Creator (section 2 of the spec).\r\n\r\nI am not sure of RoR versions and gitolit URL, so if you are able to double-check please Tracey. Thanks.',3,'2015-02-20 15:14:08',1),(11,16,'Due a check and if neccessary and update for 2014/5','','We will be investigating this system soon for an update ready for the 2014/15 RTI submissions. Hopefully there will not be any significant change.',3,'2015-02-23 12:36:26',0),(12,44,'Continuing development','','This system is in Cheshire West and Chester, Cheshire East, Coventry and looks likely to be in Islington soon. It has also been used from time-to-time by other authorities as part of consultancy provided by the Cheshire Councils.\r\n\r\nA new module will be created soon called the eSAR which is an electronic method for adult learning management organisations to carry out self-assessments and keep track of the results - a requirement brought up by Ofsted.',3,'2015-02-24 11:25:50',0),(13,50,'GUI review underway','','I am carrying out a GUI review addressing all the basic GUI and UX features and looking for simple improvements.',3,'2015-02-24 12:04:28',0),(14,4,'Development continues','','We are currently looking to include primary and secondary project code categories in the Quickfilter so that managers can quickly assess performance against these criteria.',3,'2015-02-25 12:43:32',0),(15,27,'Virtual Learning Environment continuing use','','Cheshire East Adult Learning continue to use the Moodle facility to a small extent. They haven\'t developed really significant integration of the system into their procedures and could probably do with some further consultation in this regard.',3,'2015-02-26 11:18:12',0),(16,15,'Company Magazine','','I have created a company magazine where I will post web pages of interest. Please \'Follow\'. And send through any links which might be of interest.\r\n\r\nhttps://flipboard.com/@terrabase/terrabase-company-magazine-aj26hkg3y',3,'2015-02-26 16:26:46',0),(17,26,'An old Moodle that is now archived','','This Moodle was for the whole Cheshire County Council adult learning but since the creation of the unitary authorities this Moodle has been archived and all activity has been moved over to the Cheshire East Learning moodle',3,'2015-02-27 08:21:30',0),(18,46,'Development continues','','Cryptex 2.0 is an advanced version of the Cryptex secure file sharing portal we have developed for the Cheshire Councils. It takes the Cryptex concept of encrypted file transfer and applies rules to files in identified formats such as returns. It checks the data in the returns (Excel spreadsheets) and gives feedback to the user uploading the file as to the quality of the data.\r\n\r\nThis system is due for comprehensive further development including the groups concept from Cryptex 1.0, a wider range of return types and links to QSys and ALDAS to verify tutors, providers and project codes etc.',3,'2015-03-02 12:45:38',0),(19,18,'Still widely used for its group management features','','This system was due to be taken over by Cryptex 2, only it retains a useful feature which has not yet been implemented into Cryptex 2. Staff like the group management facility and being able to create their own discrete groups of users to share files with. Development of this feature into Cryptex 2 is scheduled for over the next few months, at which point we expect Cryptex 1 to be fully superseded.',3,'2015-03-03 08:32:50',0),(20,34,'Development continues','','QSys is a very active development which is constantly evolving. The latest developments make action management much more comprehensive adding to the thoroughness of provider and tutor quality tracking.\r\n\r\nForthcoming developments on this include a facility to group providers so that actions can be copied to multiple providers in one go and analysis can take place across these groups.\r\n\r\nQSys is the definitive source of provider and tutor information and is positioned to feed this data to the other modules in the IPMS suite.',3,'2015-03-04 08:32:37',0),(21,49,'New development planned','','RPM is set to become the focus for development over the spring/summer with a facility to provide the Council Workzone department the ability to support unemployed people more effectively and help them get back into work.\r\n\r\nRPM will create accounts for each individual and allow snapshots of their situations to be built up through organisations across the region. The system requires a full audit trail so that candidates\' details can be checked over time with a record of who entered the information. Lots of data-inputters will be involved many of whom are voluntary workers with little time for training and feedback.',3,'2015-03-05 12:01:06',0),(22,45,'New management','','New management is taking over this system and we are changing the forwarding email. There are some tiny pieces of outstanding work on this regarding email sending which we are sorting shortly...',3,'2015-03-06 14:07:02',0),(23,6,'New task management system','','There are all sorts of plans coalescing into place for the Terrabase infrastructure at the moment. Redmine and the issue management strategy has been radically overhauled and the new processes are coming into play over the next few weeks. We hope to be able to put all issues into Redmine and enable people to pick off whichever issues they want to work on over the next \'sprint\'.\r\n\r\nTied into this it should be possible to create a more accurate development timeline and make it easier to produce expected completion dates for customers together with adding to the quality of the product they receive. The new system is scalable so that we can increase capacity without reaching the same kind of time limitations that we experience at the moment.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll have proper documents/meetings/training in place to explain all this, but in the meantime hopefully all the notifications coming through from Redmine aren\'t too distracting.',3,'2015-03-09 12:00:30',0),(24,15,'New compulsory fields added','','I have added a couple of new fields - as I\'m sure you have already noticed I added a field called Source a week or so ago, and I have just added a field called Skills.\r\n\r\nWhen you close an issue you will be forced to enter a value for both these fields. If you know the Source (e.g. an email with a date, a phone call with a date, a meeting with a date, testing etc) then please enter it. If you do not know the precise source then put Distant Past.\r\n\r\nPlease select one or more skills that the issue belongs to. If you feel there is a skill that is not in the list then select (N/A - please revise) and we\'ll look into adding a skill to the list.',3,'2015-03-10 10:38:26',0);
