0),(48,'Imperial Horizons Management','The system provides the core facilities to enable the management of student information as it relates to Imperial Horizons courses. To this end it provides a facility to manage course information including the facility to split courses into groups of students and define the classes those groups will attend.\r\n\r\nThe system allows managers to keep track of students’ contact information, enrol them onto courses, or withdraw them, and keep track of their progress whilst they are on the Imperial Horizons programme.\r\n\r\nThe second main area of functionality is to provide lecturers with a real-time electronic registration system where registers can be taken in front of students using an Internet connected device. To this end the system must be simple and quick and take into account the pressured environment of a lecture theatre.\r\n\r\nThe system includes other functionality to allow information such as registration information to be imported from spreadsheets, and for data to be exported to provide information for further analysis and other systems.\r\n\r\nThe design aims to present a fresh, modern approach which, as well as being capable on traditional PCs and Mac, is also compatible with touch-screen devices of varying sizes. \r\n\r\n*Electronic Documentation:* \"General Internal Project Share\":https://www.dropbox.com/sh/o0yjdtta5rd14nl/AADeAraI771lI-s0bk7dMOQza?dl=0\r\n*Paper Documentation:* Imperial Horizons folder\r\n*Edge:* \"imperialhorizons.org/edge\":https://imperialhorizons.org/edge/login\r\n*Live:* \"imperialhorizons.org\":https://imperialhorizons.org\r\n*Support expiry:* 31/09/2015\r\n*Contacts:*\r\n- \"Maggie Causley - Manager of Centre for Co-Curricular Studies\":http://www.terrabase.co.uk/redmine/attachments/download/289/MaggieCausley.vcf\r\n- \"Claire Stapley - Manager of Centre for Co-Curricular Studies\":http://www.terrabase.co.uk/redmine/attachments/download/290/ClaireStapley.vcf\r\n- \"Jackie Twitchett - Imperial Horizons Administrator\":http://www.terrabase.co.uk/redmine/attachments/download/288/JackieTwitchett.vcf\r\n*Terrabase Project Owner:* TH\r\n*Terrabase Senior Developer:* TM\r\n*Technologies:*\r\n- Ruby (version 1.9.3-p194)\r\n- Rails (version 3.2.21)\r\n*Gitolite URL:* git@www.terrabase.co.uk:imperial.git\r\n*SSL expiry*: 27/10/2015\r\n*Domain information (URL | Expiry | Package)*\r\n- www.imperialhorizons.org | 26/09/2015 | Server A8i (48761172)','',0,47,'2013-06-12 16:19:01','2015-02-23 19:22:06','imperialhorizonsmanagementsystem',1,27,28,0),(49,'RPM','','',0,44,'2013-07-01 15:55:21','2013-07-01 15:55:21','rpm',1,51,52,0),(50,'ART Diagnostic Tool','The ART diagnostic tool provides a facility for Chester Voluntary Action and their partners to assess and help their clients achieve the highest possible standards for organisational quality.\r\n\r\nThe system consists of a core diagnostic tool which gathers information about the client through a series of questions which gradually build up a profile culminating in an outcome report. The report displays graphically the client’s strengths and weakness and provides a snapshot which can be used to assess their progression in future assessments.\r\nDepending upon the outcomes from the diagnostic tool the system will also build up a toolkit for the client which they can use to address any of the concerns highlighted. The toolkit will consist of documents, online tools and links to facilities and resources which can help the client. It can be emailed as a complete package.\r\n\r\nThe system manages a list of clients keeping a historical record of previous assessments so that progression can be monitored and in the future reports can be developed taking advantage of the information collected.\r\n\r\nThe design aims to present a fresh, modern approach which, as well as being capable on traditional PCs and Macs, is also compatible with touch-screen devices of varying sizes. The system is Internet-based and stores the records centrally in cloud-based infrastructure meaning the results are available anywhere there is a connection and are always up to date.\r\n\r\n*Electronic Documentation:* \"ARTTool Dropbox share\":https://www.dropbox.com/sh/m2smw4e2lxznhzx/AADf4SgnrtqrRu3itl_Y8_B_a?dl=0\r\n*Paper Documentation:* Chester Voluntary Action folder\r\n*Forums:*\r\n\"General discussion forum\":http://www.terrabase.co.uk/redmine/projects/art/boards/87\r\n\"Ideas forum\":http://www.terrabase.co.uk/redmine/projects/art/boards/88\r\n\"Features and functionality forum\":http://www.terrabase.co.uk/redmine/projects/art/boards/9\r\n\"Future development forum\":http://www.terrabase.co.uk/redmine/projects/art/boards/26\r\n\"Sprint meeting reports forum\":http://www.terrabase.co.uk/redmine/projects/art/boards/89\r\n*Edge:* www.arttool.org.uk/edge\r\n*Live:* www.arttool.org.uk\r\n*Support expiry:* 01/09/2016\r\n*Contacts:*\r\n- \"Carol Berry - Client Project Manager\":http://www.terrabase.co.uk/redmine/attachments/download/284/CarolBerry.vcf\r\n- \"Paul Davies - Technical Manager\":http://www.terrabase.co.uk/redmine/attachments/download/285/PaulDavies.vcf\r\n*Terrabase Project Owner:* TH\r\n*Terrabase Senior Developer:* TM\r\n*Technologies:*\r\n- Ruby (version 1.9.3-p194)\r\n- Rails (version 3.2.21)\r\n*Gitolite URL:* @git@www.terrabase.co.uk:artdt.git@\r\n*SSL expiry*: N/A\r\n*Domain information (URL | Expiry | Package)*\r\n- www.arttool.org.uk | 03/10/2016 | Server A8i (48761172)','www.arttool.org.uk',0,15,'2013-08-21 14:10:37','2015-02-24 12:05:28','art',1,4,5,0),(51,'GP Secure','','',0,15,'2014-10-20 15:16:01','2014-10-20 15:16:01','gpsecure',1,24,25,0),(52,'Redmine','Development of Redmine','',0,6,'2015-02-09 11:17:35','2015-02-09 11:17:35','redmine',1,67,68,0);
