INSERT INTO `wiki_contents` VALUES (2,2,6,'h1. Research\r\n\r\nReading of Excel Spreadsheet can be done using the roo gem (\"hmcgowan-roo\":http://github.com/hmcgowan/roo)\r\nRoo causing encoding errors once hpricot installed. issue with google spreadsheet compatability swapping to spreadsheet gem http://spreadsheet.rubyforge.org/GUIDE_txt.html\r\n\r\nNeed to embed a generated pdf in a div?','','2009-12-15 18:12:15',3),(3,3,6,'h1. Home\r\n\r\n[[Research]]\r\n\r\n[[API for uploading spreadsheets from desktop Aldas]]\r\n\r\nVersions\r\n[[version 1.0]]\r\n[[version 0.5]]\r\n[[version 0.4]]\r\n[[version 0.3]]\r\n[[version 0.2]]\r\n[[version 0.1]]','','2010-08-27 15:28:52',5),(4,4,6,'h1. Version 0.2\r\n\r\n\r\nNext Release with Additional Functionality\r\nGit Commit commit:539a332607c111957ddc8a93617cbcb3456606c4\r\n\r\n    * Feature  #8: Learner Level\r\n    * Feature #17: Manage Priorities\r\n    * Feature #28: Manage Course Codes\r\n    * Feature #32: Manage Providers\r\n    * Feature #33: Manage Venues\r\n    * Feature #34: Manage tutors\r\n    * Feature #54: Email Terrabase on error.\r\n\r\nPartially implemented\r\n    * Feature #53: Import of spreadsheet\r\nBasically just to read spreadsheet and create learner record with a few fields set. Spreadsheet import runs in background, the job is automatically on successful save of import.\r\nscript/delayed_job start needs to be run to start the daemon.\r\n','','2010-01-26 17:41:29',5),(5,5,6,'h1. Version 0.1\r\n\r\nFirst release for overall design review\r\nGit Commit  commit:c5052d05313b3f262623df346e37ab8b37bdc834\r\n\r\n    * Feature #3: user authentication\r\n    * Feature #4: Manage Age Levels\r\n    * Feature #5: Import Learner Data\r\n    * Feature #6: User authorisation\r\n    * Feature #35: Manage Progressions\r\n\r\n','','2010-01-26 17:41:41',4),(6,6,6,'h1. Version 0.3\r\n\r\nGit Commit commit:92bc5b5612f9d442b2b7dc65fb5675ea6498f0ce\r\n\r\nImport of Spreadsheet #53 mostly working, Some errors generated that shouldn\'t and some missing that should be generated. Special Rules 1 and 3 ,and  RecordCount in autopart not implemented.','','2010-01-26 17:41:13',5),(7,7,6,'h1. Home\r\n\r\n','','2011-09-08 12:22:08',3),(10,10,6,'h1. Version 0.4\r\n\r\nPartial top level report\r\n\r\nCommit commit:e1b5c923d182a4a193b49522fde9384f3f89c6d8','','2010-01-27 16:16:52',3),(11,11,6,'h1. Version 0.5\r\n\r\nRelease for clients basic functionality must be in place','','2010-01-26 17:40:42',2),(12,12,6,'h1. Version 1.0\r\n\r\nFirst controlled release ','','2010-06-07 17:21:21',3),(15,15,6,'h1. Home\r\n\r\n[[Dynamic Cloud Server]]\r\n\r\n[[iptables]]\r\n\r\n[[List of Databases]]\r\n\r\n[[Backup]]','','2010-06-03 18:01:34',2),(16,16,6,'h1. Dynamic Cloud Server\r\n\r\n{{toc}}\r\n\r\nh2. Specification\r\n\r\n2 Cores, 2GB Ram 200GB HDD (root 950M, usr 4.7G, var 4.7G, home 175G)\r\n\r\nOperating System - Ubuntu 8.04 LTS minimal\r\n\r\nIp address - 82.165.130.71  s15401259.onlinehome-server.info\r\n\r\nh2. Software\r\n\r\nPackages Installed - Apache2, MySql 5.0, PHP 5, Ruby 1.8.6, Git-core 1.5.4.3, monit, build-essential, exim4, phpmyadmin.\r\n\r\nSoftware installed manually - RubyGems 1.3.7. \r\n\r\nGems installed - fastthread 1.0.7, hirb 0.3.2, mysql 2.8.1, passenger 2.2.11, rack 1.1.0 & 1.0.1, rake 0.8.7, RedCloth 4.2.3 & 3.0.4\r\n\r\nh2. Configuration\r\n\r\nUsers - tracey, tony, git, deploy.\r\n\r\nWeb applications are stored in /home/www, cronjobs for web applications are under user deploy.\r\n\r\nGit repositories are in /home/git/repositories\r\n\r\nMonit (port 2812) is monitoring apache2, mysql, sshd, exim4, delayed job processes for webaldas(3 versions), also disc space, cpu, memory and load averages.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','','2010-05-27 16:59:23',3),(17,17,6,'h1. Iptables    \r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n\r\nsudo iptables -I INBOUND 11 -p tcp --dport 443 -j ACCEPT\r\nsudo iptables -I INBOUND 12 -p udp --dport 443 -j ACCEPT\r\n</pre>','','2010-06-03 18:02:21',1),(18,18,6,'h1. List of Databases\r\n\r\ninformation_schema           \r\nata_pd_development           \r\nata_pd_production            \r\nbugzilla                     \r\nbuy2let                      \r\nchesterexodus_development    \r\nchesterexodus_production     \r\nchristaphobia_development    \r\nchristaphobia_production     \r\nchristophobia                \r\nclientarea_development       \r\ngoget_development            \r\ngoget_development_2          \r\nmailer                       \r\nmoonandstars_development     \r\nmoonandstars_production      \r\nmoveon_development           \r\nmoveonold                    \r\nmysql                        \r\nquickfuel_development        \r\nquickline_development        \r\nradiant_dev                  \r\nradiant_live                 \r\nradiant_test                 \r\nsecurefile_development       \r\nsecurefile_production        \r\nsecurefile_test              \r\ntest                         \r\ntonyharrisradiant_production \r\nwirraltaekwondo_development  \r\nwirraltaekwondo_production   \r\nwirraltaikwondo_production   \r\nwordpress                    \r\nworldpay - used by php for buying apps             ','','2010-06-03 18:04:06',1),(19,19,6,'h1. Backup\r\n\r\nNeed to monitor \r\n\r\n*to backup*\r\n\r\ntar cvpzf backup.tgz --exclude=/proc --exclude=/lost+found --exclude=/backup.tgz --exclude=/mnt --exclude=/sys /\r\nor for better compression but slower\r\ntar cvpjf backup.tar.bz2 --exclude=/proc --exclude=/lost+found --exclude=/backup.tar.bz2 --exclude=/mnt --exclude=/sys /\r\n\r\n*to restore* \r\ntar xvpfz backup.tgz -C /\r\nor \r\ntar xvpfj backup.tar.bz2 -C /\r\nand remake excluded directories\r\nmkdir proc\r\nmkdir lost+found\r\nmkdir mnt\r\nmkdir sys\r\n\r\n\r\n*postgres* ba\r\nsudo -u postgres pg_dump moodle > tmmoodle.sql\r\n\r\n*to restore* \r\nsudo -u postgres psql moodle < tmmoodle.sql','','2010-06-03 18:05:14',1),(20,20,6,'h1. Wiki\r\n\r\n[[Install a Moodle]]\r\n\r\n[[Classroom setup]]','','2010-08-24 16:22:36',2),(21,21,6,'h1. Classroom setup\r\n\r\n\r\nneed to set correct server and ipaddress in moodle configuration. Modules/settings only provides access to some of the config need to set some in pgsql.\r\nclassroom_server 192.168.1.101 (modules/settings)\r\nbase_swf_path http://cheshire.test/fcsapps\r\nwebserver 192.168.1.101\r\nclassroom_serverhost cheshire.test\r\nclassroom_serverip 127.0.0.1\r\n\r\nalso need to ensure fcsapps exists and flashserver\r\nneed flashmediaserver installed and running.\r\ninstall classroom actionscripts in applications of fms.\r\nneed to set correct value in  applications/classroom/scripts/location_specific_variables.asc\r\nalso need to ensure correct database login details in flashservices/services/moodle/DBService.php','','2010-06-03 18:11:00',1),(24,24,6,'h1. Install a Moodle\r\n\r\nDownload and unzip the moodle to the desired directory, ensure the apache user(www-data) has read access.\r\n\r\nconfigure a virtual host in Apache.\r\n\r\ncreate a directory  on your hard disk for Moodle to save your materials and other files you upload into your courses before you can start the installation process. \r\nsudo mkdir /home/data/moodledata\r\nsudo chown www-data:www-data /home/data/moodledata\r\n\r\nCreate a database in postgresql\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nsudo -u postgres  psql -c \"create user moodleuser;\" template1\r\nsudo -u postgres  psql -c \"alter user moodleuser with encrypted password \'yourpassword\';\" template1\r\nsudo -u postgres  psql -c \"create database moodle with template=template1 encoding = \'unicode\' owner =  moodleuser;\"\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\ncpoy config-dist.php to config.php and edit to have the correct database connection and data directory details.\r\n\r\nStart the install by accessing http://yourserver/install.php','','2010-08-24 16:56:00',1),(25,25,6,'h1. API for uploading spreadsheets from desktop Aldas\r\n\r\nEach user has an API token (single_access_token) which can be used by admins to use Desktop Aldas to upload a spreadsheet into a newly created Analysis.\r\n\r\nDesktop Aldas needs to POST to http://www.terrabase.co.uk/aldas_edge/imports\r\n\r\nIt also needs to pass the following:\r\n\r\nuser_credentials - API token\r\nimport[spreadsheet] - the spreadsheet to be imported\r\nimport[aid_file_id] - the id or name of the aid file to be used in the import\r\n\r\nThe following fields are optional and if not given will use their default values\r\n\r\nanalysis_name - the name of the analysis (defaults to New Analysis date time)\r\nbase_analysis - the id of the analysis to be used as the base (defaults to the id of the first analysis)\r\nimport[name] - the name of the import (defaults to same as WebAldas)\r\nimport[term] - the term the import refers to (defaults to same as WebAldas)\r\nimport[year] - the year the import refers to (defaults to same as WebAldas)\r\nimport[reference_date_string] - the reference date formatted as dd/mm/yyyy (Defaults to today)\r\n\r\nOnce uploaded the spreadsheet will automatically be imported just the same as if it had been manually imported.\r\n\r\nThe process will return one of several values\r\nSuccess - Everything worked and the Analysis and import were successfully created/uploaded, the spreadsheet is queued for processing.\r\nUnauthorised Access - either the API token is invalid, or is for a non admin user, or the url is wrong.\r\nFail - this will be followed by a list of error messages indicating which fields have issues.\r\nUnable to create Analysis - This means there was a problem creating the analysis it will be followed by a list of errors describing the issues.\r\n','','2010-09-13 12:36:03',2),(26,26,6,'h1. Wiki\r\n\r\n[[edge settings]]','','2010-12-20 18:30:11',1),(27,27,6,'h1. Edge settings\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n$CFG->dbtype    = \'pgsql\';      // \'pgsql\', \'mysqli\', \'mssql\' or \'oci\'\r\n$CFG->dblibrary = \'native\';     // \'native\' only at the moment\r\n$CFG->dbhost    = \'localhost\';  // eg \'localhost\' or \'db.isp.com\' or IP\r\n$CFG->dbname    = \'moodle_ce_edge\';     // 